title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown butter in pan slightly. Add onion and mushrooms.
After all are browned, add and simmer for 15 minutes the chicken, celery, broth, soy sauce and sugar.
(Cut down on the sugar.) Blend in the cornstarch and water that have been mixed together until smooth.
Cook the chow mein mixture until slightly thickened and clear looking.
Serves 4.

title: apple crisp(the easy, low-fat version)
directions: Slice apples and soak in juice concentrate with 1 to 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Mix dry ingredients with enough juice concentrate to moisten into a crumbly dough-like texture that you will place on top of the apples in a casserole dish covered with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Eat with a low-fat cream or frozen yogurt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in medium pieces.
Chop onion; mix with 3 tablespoons butter.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover tight.
Cook in oven about 30 minutes until squash is tender at 350°.
Take out and put cheese on top; let melt.
Mix 1/2 cup melted butter with cracker crumbs.
Place on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: hamburger and potato pie
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add beef and brown well.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Pour into a quart casserole.
Combine potatoes, egg yolk and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy. Spread over meat mixture in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: johnny's salsa cruda
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best is used fresh but will keep up to 24 hours.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Can also be put into canning jars and sealed.

title: fast and easy mexican chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except Doritos in large bowl.
Mix well.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Pour mixture over layered Doritos.
Sprinkle crushed Doritos over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Cook until soft (not too soft). Drain water.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over potatoes.
Add mustard and stir until potatoes are coated.
Add parsley and serve warm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large pan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stir in soup and asparagus.
Cook until warm.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with rice. Pour mixture over rice and sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blackberry bundt cakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in prepared Bundt pan.

title: macadamia and pineapple rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in flameproof casserole over medium heat; add rice. Stir until butter coats rice.
Add garlic and stir a few seconds but not long enough for rice to change color.
Add red and yellow peppers and cook a few seconds but not long enough for peppers to change color.
Add stock; bring mixture gently to a boil.
Add raisins, Macadamias, sage and salt.
Cover; bake 18 minutes at 375°.
Remove dish from oven.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Add cilantro and pineapple.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat milk, butter and cheese; pour over frozen potatoes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and place in greased casserole.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until dark amber color.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir vigorously and pour into buttered pans.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon and remove from skillet.
To bacon drippings, add remaining ingredients, except lettuce and eggs.
Bring sauce to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over lettuce immediately and cover for at least 1 minute, until lettuce wilts.
Sprinkle with minced eggs and crumbled bacon.
Serve at once.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture and stir until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all together and pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts; let chill overnight.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and syrup 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn in large baking pans.
Stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: "no weep" meringue
directions: In small saucepan, mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add boiling water and sugar and cook, stirring until thick and clear. Cool; add vanilla.
Beat 3 egg whites until soft peaks.
Slowly pour cooled cooked mixture over beaten egg whites; beat well. Spread on pie and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool in oven with door open.

title: roosevelt beans
directions: For thicker product, drain liquid from beans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in unbaked pie shell. Mix sugar, syrup, and vanilla together. Add melted butter. Beat whole eggs together and mix well. Pour over pecans which have been placed in pie shell. Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: honey-grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Trin fat from tenderloin.
Butterfly tenderloins by making a lengthwise cut in each, cutting to within 1/4-inch of other side. Place in large Ziploc plastic bag.

title: sugar and spice fruit cup
directions: Place fruit in serving bowl; combine the sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over fruit and toss gently.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and sprinkle with flour. Sift flour; measure and sift 3 times with next 3 ingredients. Combine egg and milk and mix with fork.
Add all at once with dry ingredients, stirring quickly, until flour is dampened, but not smooth.
Wash, dry and cut cranberries.
Toss with the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Quickly stir in cranberries and nuts just to distribute.
Turn into prepared pan, pushing dough into corners. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 20 minutes.
Increase heat to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until nicely browned.
Remove from pan to wire rack to cool before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf and has no fat.

title: copper pennies
directions: After cooking carrots, drain and set aside.
Slice onion and green pepper.
Mix with tomato soup, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Heat to boiling and pour over drained carrots.
Can be served hot, but also good cold a day or so later.

title: no cook fudge balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together with peanut butter.
Mix real good.
Add vanilla and melted butter; mix well.
Shape into approximately 1-inch balls and roll in crushed nuts.
Place on large, foil-lined cookie sheet and freeze 20 minutes.
Remove from freezer and store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushroom caps with damp cloth and remove stems.
Mix remaining ingredients and stuff in mushroom caps.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix well hash browns, sour cream, soup, cheese and onion.
Press into a sprayed casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes and oleo until well blended.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. Mix bran with milk until bran is moistened.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add egg and oil, beating until blended.
Add flour mixture, stirring until combined.
Do not over mix.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: mamall nannie's pork barbecue
directions: Boil pork 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Pork should be salted to taste while cooking.
Drain.
Cool.
Tear into small pieces. Place in large pan in 350° oven to bake out some of moisture.

title: maine blueberry muffins(diabetic recipe)
directions: Lightly coat blueberries with 2 teaspoons flour.
You can shake the flour and berries together in a paper bag.
In a large bowl, mix together the 1 3/4 cups flour, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a small bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Add oil, orange juice and grated rind.
Add the liquid to dry mixture and stir a few times gently.
Before the 2 mixtures are fully combined, add berries and rind.
Spoon into muffin cups coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Fill each one two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.
Exchanges:
1 starch and 1 fat.

title: dijon breaded pork chops
directions: Mix crushed crackers, salt, thyme, pepper and sage in shallow dish; set aside.
Blend egg and mustard in shallow dish.
Dip each pork chop into egg mixture, then cracker mixture to coat.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add chops.
Fry over moderate heat, 16 to 20 minutes, turning only once.

title: easy sweet potato casserole
directions: Spread pie filling in 8 x 8-inch pan. Top with sliced potatoes. Mix cranberry sauce, apricot and marmalade together and spoon over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies supreme
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add butter, sugar and eggs.
When mixed, add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat, large onion and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add 1 can Ro-Tel, 1 can tomato soup, 1 package taco seasoning and 1 can mushrooms (stems and pieces); blend well. Add Velveeta cheese and blend until completely melted.
Stir in 2 cups cooked rice.
Simmer.

title: sleepy butterscotch bars
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add sugar; stir well.
Add marshmallows; cook until marshmallows melt, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal.
Press cereal mixture evenly into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Yield:
18 servings.
(Serving 1 x 3 x 2-inch bars.)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in 1/2 cup of salted water until tender.
Drain.
Mix together 1 cup mayonnaise and 4 ounces Cheez Whiz.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Crush 1 roll of Ritz crackers and spread on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles up.

title: hot crab canapes
directions: Fold mayonnaise and crab into egg white.
Season to taste with Worcestershire, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate. Toast bread.
Just before serving, spread with crab mixture, then sprinkle with paprika.
Broil for 2 or 3 minutes, until puffed and delicately browned; serve at once.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: salmon dip appetizer
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Chill overnight, covered, for full flavor.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm wheat or butter thins crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain off excess water.
Add soup mix, chopped water chestnuts, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350° or until set and lightly browned.

title: cold day potato soup
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and carrots.
Dice onion and celery. Add 5 cups of water.
Cook until nearly tender, not mushy.
Add chicken bouillon cubes and evaporated milk.
Add butter and parsley flakes.
Season to taste.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add together and heat.
Serve with dill pickles, barbecue bread and potato chips.

title: pot roast with vegetable gravy
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Brown well in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Remove meat and add celery, onion, carrots and garlic to oil.
Saute until tender (do not brown).
Add bouillon cube, 1 cup water, tomato sauce and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Return meat to pot.
Cover.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
(May be cooked on top of stove, if covered tightly.) Remove meat and keep warm. Skim off excess fat.
Combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil, boil 1 minute. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bowen avenue salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Process on low for 30 seconds.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir well before serving on salad.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (with peelings on); cool and peel, then cube and combine with other vegetables and eggs.
Mix herbs, spices and relish with mayonnaise and sour cream.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients together and chill.

title: edna's casserole
directions: Dice onion and add to ground beef.
Brown hamburger and onion. Drain.
Add Ranch Style beans (drain first) and Spanish rice. Slice green and black olives in half and arrange on top of casserole.
Tear or cut cheese in strips and arrange on top of casserole also.
Bake in 350° oven until the cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: breaded steak
directions: Flatten steaks	into
nice
serving portions.
Mix eggs and cheese together.
Dip
steak
into	egg mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Coat well.
Fry
quickly
in hot oil.
Place on paper towel to remove any excess oil.
This is good with fried potatoes or with side dish of spaghetti and a salad.

title: joe's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, brown the meat with garlic and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer all day, stirring occasionally.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Blenderize for 2 minutes.
Grease 9-inch glass pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
(Usually takes 30 minutes or more until it looks set in middle.)

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil water with pinch of salt.
When boiling, add butter. When melted, add chopped cabbage.
When cabbage is completely cooked, set aside and let cool overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti deluxe
directions: Boil hen the day before.
Debone and cut into large pieces. Reserve broth.
Saute vegetables in oleo for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, pimento and seasonings.
Simmer 30 more minutes.
Add chicken.
Cook spaghetti in reserved broth until broth is absorbed.
Mix with chicken mixture.
Top with olives and cheese.
Serves 12.

title: noodles
directions: For 3 eggs, use 2 cups flour and 3 tablespoons milk.
Mix ingredients together.
Roll out, then let stand until partly dry. Cut into thin strips.
Cook in broth until done.

title: ladies hot luncheon sandwich
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter 8 slices of bread.
Arrange in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top each slice with meat and cheese.
Top with remaining slices of bread.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over sandwiches and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, sprinkle with corn flakes and melted butter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients in electric blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in a greased 9-inch pie dish; let set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Eat warm or cold.

title: potato goody
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes; mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: roast pork with apple topping
directions: In a small bowl, combine the flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, mustard, caraway seed, sugar, pepper and sage; rub over roast. Cover and let stand 30 minutes.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Split cucumbers lengthwise with skins left on.
Put cucumbers in a crock.
Add salt and 1 gallon boiling water.
When cool, cover with plate.
Let stand 1 week.
If mold forms, remove. Drain and add another gallon of boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Dissolve alum in 1 gallon of boiling water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and discard liquid.
Combine vinegar, sugar and mixed spices.
Bring to boiling point.
Put in cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Drain in large pan; bring to boiling point (vinegar mixture) and put over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Follow last step at least 3 times.
The pickles are then ready to use or can be packed in hot jars and sealed.

title: jello salad
directions: In a pan over low-medium heat, melt marshmallows in the milk. After they are melted stir in Jell-O.
Take off heat and mix well. Cool.
It will get very thick, almost hard.
Make Dream Whip and add the cream cheese to the Dream Whip while beating it; combine Dream Whip, Jell-O mixture and fruit cocktail together; place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set.

title: easy-make fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Mix fruit, vanilla and sugar.
Options:
1/2 cup peaches, 1/2 cup blackberries or 3/4 cup cherries.
Heat oven to 450°; put butter in pan; place pan in oven.
Heat until bubbly, almost brown.
Quickly pour in batter, then fruit.
Cook for 30 minutes at 450°.
Reduce temperature to 350°, cook 30 more minutes.

title: jennifer's dad's favorite peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches and 1/4 cup sugar in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Mix 1 cup sugar, oleo, eggs, flour and vanilla, then stir into warm peaches.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: First brown hamburger just until red disappears.
Then add garlic, bell pepper and chopped onion and continue to brown hamburger all through.
Drain all grease and juices from hamburger. Hamburger must be as dry as possible.
Recommend to use paper towel in bowl to soak up grease.
Put hamburger in 2-inch deep 15 x 10-inch baking dish (if possible or bigger) and spread out thoroughly.
Cover with mushroom soup (do not mix, just cover). Spread out.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Set Tater Tots carefully on top so soup and hamburger are completely covered.
Bake until Tots are brown.
Add cheese and bake for 30 minutes more.
Dish serves 5.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook slowly in a heavy crock-pot until thick.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: baked sausage and eggs
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Combine cooked and drained sausage, onion, tomato, mushrooms and bread cubes in baking dish.
In large bowl combine eggs, milk and basil, pepper and garlic powder and mix well.
Pour egg mixture over sausage mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle both cheeses evenly over egg mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook the first 2 ingredients over medium heat until light browned.
Drain. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer about 5 minutes. Spoon on hamburger buns.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed on package.
Drain and cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook in medium size pot the sugar, cocoa and milk on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Bring to a rolling boil; cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: On stove, melt butter on low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla, and eggs.
Mix well, set aside.
In medium bowl, add flour, baking powder, salt, and
baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle 1/2 c. chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise with salt and dash of pepper.
Chill.

title: wedding casserole
directions: Slice all vegetables thinly.
In 2-quart casserole layer using 1/2 the vegetables in the following way.

title: mint-lemon iced tea
directions: Boil 5 cups water, sugar, lemon juice and peel and mint together for 5 minutes.
Steep tea bags in 5 cups boiling water for 5 minutes.
Combine mixtures and chill.
Serve over ice with extra mint, if desired.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix instant pudding with 3 cups milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread this mixture over crackers.	Place another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding mixture.
Melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa, confectioners sugar and water.
Mix until smooth.
Spread on top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mama tucker's boiled custard
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour, vanilla and milk. Cook until slightly thick. Let it get cold. Beat egg whites and beat into custard.

title: lemon-parsley new tatos
directions: Pare a strip from the center of each new potato.
Heat 1 inch salted water (1/4 teaspoon salt, if desired, to 1 cup water) to boiling in 3-quart saucepan; add potatoes.
Cover and heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender; drain.
Return potatoes to saucepan.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Put cider and cranberry juice in 30 cup coffee maker.
Put sugar and spices in coffee basket.
Perk as you would for coffee. Serve hot.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown chicken and place in baking pan. Mix tomatoes, soup mix and wine together and pour over chicken. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When done, sprinkle cheese over top. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute onion slowly in butter for 3 minutes.
Add beef and cook over low heat until brown.
Blend in salt, pepper, milk and peas. Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
Make biscuits from
Bisquick mix.
Place on top of meat.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes until Bisquick biscuits are well browned.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Combine in large bowl, eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Layer chiles and cheese (except for part of Cheddar) in glass baking pan.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm and golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Combine remaining sugar with cinnamon, mixing well. Roll each ball in cinnamon mixture.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until the first cookie begins to fall.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well and add:

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In prepared baking dish, alternate layers of thinly sliced potatoes, onion, cheese, salt, pepper and butter.
Combine soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: curley macaroni salad
directions: Pour oil over warm macaroni. Mix sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, parsley and pepper; shake well. Pour over macaroni and stir well. Chop fine;	celery, cucumbers, green pepper and carrot, add. Refrigerate overnight.

title: brazilian toffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy 8-inch skillet or heavy pan. When melted, add 2 cups sugar. Add Brazil nuts, water and corn syrup. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cook slowly 25-35 minutes, stirring occasionally, to crack stage (hard ball), or 290°.

title: there's hardly ever any left
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Layer one:
Mix in mixer cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread in crust.
Layer two: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed.
Pour over layer one.
Layer three:
Spread with Cool Whip.
Layer four:
Sprinkle chopped nuts (optional) over.
I do half nuts and half plain.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust. Enjoy!

title: oven fries
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into long strips.
Toss in a bowl with oil until coated.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray; place potatoes on sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Turn occasionally to brown all sides.
Serves 4. Each serving contains 120 calories, 3 g protein, 3.5 g fat, 0 chol. and 8 mg sodium.

title: double pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar with eggs.
Add pecans.
Add margarine, syrups and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in preheated oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shake well.
This sauce is good on chicken.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Boil the carrots until tender in salted water.
Cool. Alternate the green pepper rings and the onion rings.
Combine and beat the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight, in covered large jars.
Serve as needed.

title: no-peekie stew
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours.
Prepare rice 20 minutes before stew is done.
Serve with stew on top of rice.

title: microwave potato casserole(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Peel and slice or dice potatoes. In large bowl, mix potatoes, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. Pour half of mixture in large casserole; dot with 1/2 of butter. Add rest of potato mixture; dot with remaining butter. Salt and pepper mixture; cover. Cook in microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir; recover and cook for 15 to 20 more minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with soup and Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bavarian dumplings(germany)
directions: Chop the bacon.
Heat the oil and fry the bacon pieces until golden brown.
Cut up the rolls and put them in a bowl.
Heat the milk and pour it over the bread.
Stir in the eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and bacon.
With damp hands, form little balls from the dough.
Half-fill a big pan with water and bring to a boil.
Turn off the heat and drop in the dumplings.
Leave for about 20 minutes.
When they bob up to the surface, they're ready.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Shredding potatoes is easy compared to shredding carrots but they do discolor.
Put them in cool water and then drain.
Mix them with salt, pepper and onion and pour half and half over to just barely cover.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Great with most fruits.

title: tex-mex salad
directions: Toss onion, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese in Italian dressing; set aside.
Brown meat.
Add drained beans and vegetable seasoning; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix with cold salad.
Toss in crushed tortilla chips and avocado slices.
Garnish with olives, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: health salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling and cold water.
Refrigerate jello until set.
Add pineapple.
Fold in sour cream and pecans.
Add cherries for color.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Use flowerets of broccoli, wash and cut in chunks.
Cook broccoli and onion in chicken broth until almost tender.
Add 1/2 package fine noodles.
Cook until tender.
Add water if necessary. Cut cheese in chunks and add to soup.
Heat until cheese melts. Serve hot.
Enjoy!

title: ham-cheese-poppy seed rolls
directions: Combine margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mustard.
Slice packages of rolls as one.
Spread top and bottom with spread.
Place layer of ham on bottom.
Top with layer of cheese.
Replace top layer of rolls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.
(Also freezes well.)

title: mushroom cap appetizers
directions: Remove mushroom stems; mince.
Place caps rounded side down on cookie sheet.
Drain clams; save liquid. Over medium heat melt butter and brush on mushroom caps.
In remainder of butter, saute stems, garlic and clam juice until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in clams, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Tuck into mushrooms.
Broil 8 minutes.

title: crab chantilly
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch quiche pan. Use a rolling pin to crush 1/2 package of crackers in a plastic bag.
Whisk together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon rind, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in the shredded crab and spread in a quiche pan.
Top with the almonds, then the crumbs, the Parmesan cheese and a generous sprinkle of paprika.

title: party apple dip
directions: Cream all ingredients except apples.
Serve with Granny Smith apple slices.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice and sugar together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place in mold or paper-lined muffin tins.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer abut 20 minutes before serving.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Trim dark green and pink parts from rind; cut into 1-inch squares.
Measure 6 cups.
Soak overnight in solution of salt and 1 quart water.
Drain and rinse.
Cover with cold water.
Cook for 25 minutes, until tender.

title: sunday chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soups, 1/4 cup butter and rice. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Brush with remaining butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade applesauce cake with homemade applesauce
directions: Put apple slices into a large saucepan.
Grate lemon zest into the pan.
Cover and stew the apples over low heat until tender, 30 minutes.
Mash the apples with a potato masher and squeeze in lemon juice.
Stir in sugar and butter and simmer uncovered until thickened.
Stays fresh in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill cans 1/2 full. Cover with tinfoil and steam 2 to 3 hours. I set cans in water. Slice cold and steam before eating. (I use cans 3 or 4-inches in diameter.)

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Debone chicken and place in a baking dish in bite-size pieces.
Mix soup and broth; add 1/2 stick margarine and pour over chicken.
Mix flour and milk.
Pour over previous mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Place ground beef and garlic in 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes, or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Blend in water, tomato paste, tomato sauce, oregano, salt, sugar, basil and pepper.
Cook, covered, on full power 6 to 8 minutes, or until boiling.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Blend cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley flakes in a small bowl.
Layer half of noodles in 2-quart utility dish.
Spread noodles with half of cheese mixture, half of Mozzarella cheese and half of meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover loosely with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Heat, covered, on full power for 13 to 16 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle top generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press in pan the crescent rolls; bake until brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch dressing; put on top of crust. Chop up raw vegetables; press into crust.
Top with grated cheese.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine taco mix with water; combine dressing mix with water.
Combine all ingredients, except the meat and onions.
When all is mixed and warm, add meat and onions. Simmer 45 minutes.	Top with nachos and grated cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Old, almost rotten bananas which have been peeled and frozen are best.
Thaw bananas in microwave, mash with liquid from thawing and set aside.
Cream softened margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, soda and vanilla.
Add sour milk.
Stir in mashed bananas. Add flour and chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until top of loaf is golden brown and springs up when touched with finger.

title: pork chop and green bean casserole
directions: Brown chops in butter. Mix beans, soup and milk. Pour mixture into 2-quart baking dish. Arrange chops on top. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: jason's good bars
directions: Let sugar and Karo come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Pour over corn flakes.
Take a teaspoonful and drop on waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: turkey and rice dressing
directions: Remove neck and giblets; place in 3 1/2 cup chicken broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Reserve broth in a 5 to 8-quart Dutch oven. Melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onions, celery and peppers. Add parsley, chestnuts, apples, currants, pine nuts, cinnamon, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and Mahatma rice.
Mix thoroughly. In microwave, heat 2 packages of French's brown gravy mix with 2 cups turkey broth for 1 minute, stir and heat another minute.
Add to stuffing mixture and mix well.

title: banana or strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Combine cornbread mix, eggs, chopped onion, cheese, butter and seasonings.
Stir well.
Stir in broccoli (batter will be thick). Pour mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: mema's chocolate icing
directions: Boil one minute on medium heat (rolling hard boil), reserving nuts.
Use on layers of white or chocolate cake mix.
Bake as directed on box.
Sprinkle nuts on each layer.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Mix. Add half of flour and milk.
Mix and add other half of flour and milk.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: crabby burritos
directions: In one skillet, brown hamburger (sausage optional).
In another skillet, bring butter to boil on medium to medium-high. In a saucepan, melt Velveeta with picante sauce.
Add crabmeat to butter and let sit until warm enough to separate.
As crabmeat gets stringy, add red pepper and bring to a golden brown. Drain hamburger meat and mix with the crabmeat.
Then you have two ways to complete the filling:

title: pig feet
directions: Clean feet real good.
Put feet in pot of water, enough to cover feet, with 5 tablespoons of salt.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, wash feet with water until salt is removed.
Put back in pot with vinegar and crushed red pepper. After it comes to a boil, cook three hours.
Put feet in platter. Sprinkle with black pepper and salt, if needed.
Invite five more people and enjoy yourself.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Mash bananas; add to sugar mixture.
Add eggs; stir.
Add flour and baking soda.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: jello pie
directions: Combine sugar and fruit juice and bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Cool.
Beat	1
can chilled Pet milk and add to mixture.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bourbon souffle
directions: To well beaten egg yolks, add bourbon.
To stiffly beaten egg whites, add sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and heat in double boiler.
Pour slowly over whites and sugar, beating constantly until like divinity.
Fold yolks and whites together and pour into mold which has been rinsed in cold water.
Garnish with chopped nuts.
Chill until set.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder together; spread on bottom of 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese over this.
Top with pizza sauce, red and green peppers and the remaining 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with hard bread sticks.

title: alberta toomey's zucchini squash
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Slice zucchini thin and add to butter and onions.
Cook on low heat until squash starts to get tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and sugar.
Cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Then put in a greased baking dish.
Top with sharp cheese and bake in oven for 15 minutes.

title: corny bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
In a large mixing bowl, add all ingredients, including melted margarine.
Stir well.
Pour into pan.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 45 to 55 minutes, or until tested done.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and butter and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add honey; let stand a few minutes. Use two pie crusts, with slits in the top crust.
Begin baking at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook until crust is golden brown.
Cool a few minutes before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and bell pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix together eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper; set aside. Place both cheeses in bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Pour sausage mixture over cheese.
Pour egg mixture evenly over top of sausage and cheese to completely cover them.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° then reduce heat to 350°; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine tomato paste, celery, onion, pimento and soup; cook for 30 minutes.
Add chicken, spaghetti, salt and pepper.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: very best chocolate cake(no eggs)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Caramel Icing when cool.

title: steak and onions
directions: Brown meat on both sides; drain grease off of meat.
Pour mixture of soup, water and onions over meat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients together except potatoes.

title: old-fashion oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling browns and a knife comes out clean when inserted in the center of the pie. Cool and top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour. Gradually stir in chicken broth with wire whisk. Cook over low heat until mixture thickens. Mix egg yolks, sherry and cream. Gradually beat hot sauce into egg mixture. Reheat until sauce is hot and fold in mushrooms and turkey. Add cooked spaghetti. Pour into ovenproof serving dish and top with Parmesan cheese and almonds. Put under broiler and brown until cheese and almonds are golden. Serves 6.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool in refrigerator.
In large bowl, combine pie filling mix and sugar; add pineapple, juice and sour cream and mix thoroughly with spoon.
Pour mixture into cool pie shell and chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
When serving, garnish with whipped topping.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet pan with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Place crackers, salt side up on foil.
Bring oleo and sugar to a boil and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup of almond flavoring.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake 400° for 16 minutes.
Top with chocolate chips as soon as you remove from the oven.
Spread melted chips with spatula. Cool. Break into pieces.
Store in container.

title: chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Add sugar, flour and eggs (beaten).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased pan and bake at 350° about 25 or 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray large double grocery bag inside with Pam and put in popped corn.
Put brown sugar, margarine, light syrup and salt in large bowl.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir, then microwave 4 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and add butter flavoring and soda; stir.
Pour hot mixture over popcorn in grocery bag.
Shake bag well.
Place in microwave for 3 minutes on High; remove. Shake again.
Return to microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake well.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: quick and easy deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 15 minutes.
Cool, peel, cut in half.
Remove yolks, and mash with potato masher.
Add Thousand Island dressing to creamy consistency.
Fill eggs, garnish with paprika.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine. Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12-cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons of the melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the
nuts over bottom of prepared pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar
and	water to remaining margarine.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits;
cut
each biscuit in half and shape into a ball.
Place 20 balls in bottom of prepared pan.
Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over balls.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately onto
waxed paper
and	remove from pan.
This nutty treat serves 10.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place the items in layers, starting with the spinach and ending with the frozen peas.
Frost with the Miracle Whip and mayonnaise.
Cover with the grated Swiss cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients into paste and press into bottom of an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie shell 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake pie shell on preheated sheet for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground meat and onions; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop.
Add sugar and cherry Jell-O.
Stir well; cool.
Add celery and nuts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Serve.

title: garlic grits
directions: Combine water, grits and salt. Cook until grits are done. Add margarine and stir until melted. Add garlic cheese and stir until melted. Beat 2 eggs in a 1-cup measuring cup and add milk to fill that cup. Add to the grits mixture. Pour into a buttered casserole and cover with crumbled cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Should serve 12.

title: pasta with seafood in herb-butter sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in parsley, onion, garlic salt and pepper; simmer 2 minutes.
Add seafood to heat through.
Toss with hot pasta.
Serve immediately. Can also be made without seafood for a meatless meal.
Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, bell pepper, pimento, celery and onion.
Bring sugar and cider vinegar to a boil and boil until clear.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: mrs. griffin molasses cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices. Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add eggs.
Mix boiling water and molasses together.
Add to dry ingredients. Bake in 8-inch greased square pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken 'n biscuits casserole
directions: Cook together first 4 ingredients about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine biscuit mix and sugar in a large bowl.
Blend well. Add milk and eggs, mixing well.
If mixing by hand, about 50 to 60 strokes ought to do it!
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Pour melted butter evenly over surface.
Spoon pie filling over top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cool whip pineapple dessert(low fat)
directions: Just mix all of this up together in a bowl and keep refrigerated.
It's very simple, easy and good.
If you want the fat, use regular pudding and Cool whip.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Wash and prepare
vegetables.
Combine
vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seed and celery seed; bring to boil. Add vegetables
and simmer for
minutes.
Continue
simmering
while quickly packing in hot sterilized
jars. Fill to 1/8-inch top. Seal immediately.

title: avocado guacamole dip
directions: Clean and finely dice green onions.
Peel and finely dice tomatoes.
Then, peel and finely mash avocados.
Squeeze juice from lemon over mashed avocados; mix well.
(Lemon retards discoloration.)
Add avocados to onion, tomato mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fat-free broccoli dip
directions: In bowl, beat softened cream cheese, mustard and milk until well blended.
Stir in thawed broccoli, peppers and scallions. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill.
Serve with rice cakes, crackers, breadsticks or vegetables.

title: company chicken
directions: Spread rice in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over.
Mix together soups and water.
Arrange raw chicken on top of soups and water mixture.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. After 8 minutes, pat down with a spatula.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal.
Let
stand.
Mix
with sugar, eggs and oil.
Add alternately the
buttermilk
and dry ingredients.
Add
raisins.
Store
in
refrigerator and spoon into muffin pan as you want them.
Keeps for 6 weeks.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding (from scratch)
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Spread small amount on bottom of 1-1/2 qt.
casserole; cover with layer of Nilla Wafers. Top with layer of sliced bananas.
Pour 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each ending with custard.
Beat remaining 3 egg whites until stiff, but not dry; gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Pile on top of pudding covering entire surface.
Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) 5 minutes or until delicately browned.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yield:
8 servings of 3/4 cup.

title: cheese stuffed pasta shells
directions: Brown meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Drain off fat.
Stir in sauce.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes.
Combine Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, eggs and 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella.
Stuff manicotti with cheese filling.
In a 13 x 2-inch baking dish (sprayed with Pam), arrange manicotti in single layer. Add meat sauce to completely cover.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella on top.
Cover dish with Saran Wrap and cook on Medium-high for 30 to 35 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 7 servings.
Can bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: red and green layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, dissolve jello in water.
Add cranberry sauce. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Flatten chicken between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Dredge in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Pour clarified butter into frying pan and lightly brown chicken.
Add chicken stock, lemon juice and parsley.
Bring to a boil and cook for 8 minutes. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: st. mary's county stuffed ham
directions: Fill a 40-quart pot 2/3 full of water; put rack in bottom. Bring to a boil.
Meantime, chop cabbage, kale, onions and celery. Place chopped ingredients in cheesecloth and immerse in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Add all the spices in a quart jar; cover and shake well.
After 7 minutes, remove chopped greens from water; dump in shallow pan and let cool.

title: pizza cups
directions: Add tomato paste, onion and seasonings to meat.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in greased muffin cups, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mix into each muffin cup and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour and salt.
Mix coloring and cocoa; add vinegar and mix well.
Add flour mixture slowly, alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: hot appetizers
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or larger.
Beat eggs slightly with flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cottage cheese and melted butter and blend together.
Pour into melted butter pan.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cheese in microwave.
Add butter and salsa, a little at a time.
Cook for 1 minute in microwave on Medium-high. Stir.
Cook for 4 or 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Brown ham and onion together; add peas, Bloody Mary mix, water and rice.
Let cook 20 minutes.
If too thick, add more water. Add shrimp for last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking.
Serve with rolls or cornbread.

title: nona pineapple treat
directions: Combine flour, butter and cream cheese.
Mix with mixer.
Roll into walnut size balls and put into refrigerator overnight or half a day.
Roll out and press with bottom of teacup.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of pineapple preserves on each circle and roll up to a point in the middle or make a square.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° on a greased baking sheet.
Keep cold until used.

title: venison chili
directions: Fry beef fat in heavy skillet; add meat and brown.
Add seasonings.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Cook slowly 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining water as needed. Serve with pinto beans.
Serves 8.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice and you will have a good cake.

title: ribbon jello salad(very festive)
directions: Pour into dish and refrigerate until firm, about 1/2 hour. It must be firm.
Then add 1 1/3 cups white sauce on top of lime Jell-O and put in refrigerator to set.
Do the same with orange, lemon and cherry Jell-O alternating with white sauce each layer. Be sure Jell-O is set between each layer.
This does take some time to make but it's a great dessert.
It's always been a hit any time I've taken it to an event.
Use your imagination.
I have made it red and white only, in layers.
Or use just your favorite flavors of Jell-O.
Have fun!

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add onion and celery and cook over low heat until tender.
Add water or stock and bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add stuffing mix all at once, tossing lightly, until moist.

title: judy and myrna's hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add meat and brown it.
Add flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat. Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: hard rock christmas candy
directions: Mix together syrup, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil to hard-crack stage (300° on a candy thermometer).
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto a cookie sheet that has been packed well with powdered sugar.
This takes 1/2 box of sugar (press down well and make sure to cover any holes so that hot syrup won't drip through).
Allow mixture to cool.
Pick up candy and turn it over.
Cool candy until it can be broken into small pieces. Makes 2 to 3 cups of broken candy or about 36 pieces.
(This is not to be made by children unless there is adult supervision.)

title: finger salad
directions: Mix. Bake in 200 degree oven 1-1/2 hours. Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on newspapers or paper towels to cool (and to wick off any excess oil).

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade, milk and coloring.
Stir well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust and freeze until firm (about 4 hours or overnight).
Garnish with lemon slices and whipped topping as desired.
(Remove frozen pie from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to thaw slightly.) Serves 6 to 8.

title: "decorator" frosting
directions: Mix all together.
Beat well.
Great for decorating cookies. Cakes, too!
Keeps well in refrigerator for 3 or 4 days.

title: beef stew(servings: 4.  preparation time:  3 hours.)
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge meat in flour.
In a large soup kettle, brown meat in hot olive oil.
Add sugar, celery, parsley, garlic, bay leaf, tomatoes, bouillon and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer one hour. Taste and season with additional salt and pepper or herbs of your choice, if desired.
Add carrots and potatoes and continue to simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add onions and simmer until onions are tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; add other ingredients. Beat with mixer. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap olive completely in a pinch of dough.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Can be frozen, then baked.
Serve warm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion and salt. Refrigerate 12 hours. Add rest of ingredients except whipped cream, mix and put in refrigerator for 2 hours. Add whipped cream last, just before serving.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Note:
Do not use cream of onion soup.

title: cranberry bog
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags in saucepan.
Steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add cranberry juice, orange juice and sugar to tea.
Stir and heat to serving temperature.
Pour into mugs.
Garnish with a half slice of orange.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Add chicken, onion, peppers, 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Mix well. Add noodles and toss to coat. Transfer to greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheeses. Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and veggies are tender. Serves 6.

title: great artichoke casserole
directions: Cut or mash artichokes.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Add artichokes.
Place in baking dish and cook at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle paprika on top.
May also be used as a dip by adding a little extra mayonnaise and blending the artichoke slightly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix margarine with Ritz crackers and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients well and top with the cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shake 'n bake
directions: For raw meat, put 8 teaspoons salt in.

title: waffles and nuts
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add oil and eggs and mix until smooth and well mixed.
Preheat waffle irons.
Fill each section of waffle iron with mixture until brown and crisp, approximately 6 or 7 minutes.
Serve with margarine, syrup or jelly.
Makes 3 full size waffles.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and spice.
Add melted margarine, eggs and milk (add slowly until creamy).
Add vanilla last.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Crush pretzels fine.
Mix with melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set pan aside.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in Dutch oven; saute carrots, celery, onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Peel tomatoes; cut in half crosswise.
Place strainer over large bowl; remove seeds by squeezing gently.
Chop pulp and add to join in large bowl.
Add tomatoes and juice to Dutch oven.
Add oregano, basil, salt and pepper; cook 15 minutes.
Add beef broth and green beans; cook 30 minutes longer, adding zucchini and parsley after 20 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients except the broccoli and butter.
Melt butter over broccoli and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: bologna bundles
directions: Place equal amount of soup on each slice bologna.
Fold over, fasten with toothpicks.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over all and lay bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in slow cooker for 2 to 4 hours (or all day).
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: sausage ring
directions: Thaw bread (not to rise).
Cook sausage; drain.
While hot, add 1 egg, cheese and seasoning.
Mix and set aside.
Roll dough into 6 x 18-inch (pull to size).
Put meat filling in center; bring sides up and pinch on top.
Form a ring; slice every 2 to 3 inches on top (not all the way through).
Beat other egg and spread on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and let rise for 45 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into logs and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice off 1/4-inch slices and bake until light brown.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: coke roast
directions: Score roast in several places.
Fill each slit with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast on all sides in oil.
Remove. Drain or blot fat from roast.

title: beef burritos
directions: Crumble hamburger into skillet.
Add onion.
Season with salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour off fat and add chilli salsa. Place a large spoonful in the center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Fold sides over and fold up ends.
Place on a cookie sheet, folded sides down.
Cover with aluminum foil and heat in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve alone or smothered in green chilli salsa.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for 1/2 stick butter and corn flakes.
Mix 1/2 stick melted butter and crushed corn flakes; spread on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and corned beef together. Combine vodka or gin and soup mix; let onion soup absorb the liquid.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate mixture 1/2 hour, then form into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together. Will keep for up to 1 month in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Again, stir us, Lord!

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the consomme.
After Jell-O is dissolved, let cool.
Add corned beef, onion, green pepper, celery and mayonnaise.
Press into loaf pan. Top with hard-boiled eggs.

title: turner farm hickory nut pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs with a fork.
Add the syrup, sugar, vanilla and salt and beat again.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell, then sprinkle the nuts on the top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and then at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate, Crisco and margarine; set aside to cool.
Beat eggs with rotary beater and sugar; mix well.
Add chocolate mixture to eggs
and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to egg and chocolate mixture; mix well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Add rice. Simmer until golden brown. Add onions and soup.
Pour mixture into covered casserole dish.
Place in oven at 350° and bake for 1 hour or until the rice has absorbed all the consomme.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a slow boil, then cook on medium for 1 1/2 hours or until thick.
Delicious over steak, hamburger, pork chops, even scrambled eggs or fried potatoes.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Prepare fruit by thoroughly crushing, one layer at a time. Measure 2 cups into large bowl or pan.
Mix sugar into fruit; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix water and fruit pectin in small saucepan. Bring to a full boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir into fruit.
Stir 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into scalded containers, filling to within 1/2 inch of tops.
Cover; let stand at room temperature for 24 hours, then store in freezer.
Small amounts may be stored in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.
Makes 4 3/4 cups.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Add to large pot of boiling water.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomato paste.
Stir well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add shredded cheese.
Allow to melt.
Stir in rice.
Then stuff peppers.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(I always put more cheese on top during the last 5 minutes of baking time.)

title: energy treats
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add drops of water if needed.
Form into 15 balls, then roll in pretzels.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage and add chunked pineapple and unpeeled diced apple.
Toss in 2 handfuls of marshmallows.
Dissolve sugar in mayonnaise and coat cabbage mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle part of Pepperidge Farm dressing mix to line bottom of dish.
Add all ingredients and mix and put into casserole.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lucky charms microwave snacks
directions: Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Place butter and marshmallows in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 minute and 30 seconds to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press mixture in pan; cool and cut into about 2 x 2-inch bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: hearty baked potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; boil until tender.
Cut in 1/2 to 1-inch chunks.
Spread evenly into baking dish.
Combine onions, soup, parsley, mayonnaise and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle bacon on top; garnish with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lynda fisher's black russian cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
beat
minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crock pot pork loin
directions: Place sliced pork loin in bottom of crock pot.	Add spices, onions, and apple juice.
Cook on low all day.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables completely or blanch in boiling water; drain and cool.
Mix the vegetables of your choice with soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and grated cheese.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and keep warm (not boiling) to baste chicken. Serves 12.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Bring sauerkraut and seasonings to a boil.
Add pork chops or spareribs.
Peel and cut into chunks the potatoes.
Add to pot. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour or until pork and potatoes are tender.

title: esther's sugared doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 2 hours).

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish or cake pan.
Crush half of the chips and put on top of the chicken.
Add desired amount of cheese.
Mix with a mixer the soups and Ro-Tel.
Pour over chicken, chips and cheese.
Make another layer of chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is heated thoroughly. Very good.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread pie filling over cake mixture.
Mix brown sugar, butter, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: elaine's hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Blend chicken, celery, almonds, green pepper, pimento, onion salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat eggs with mixer for 3 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Fold in pumpkin.
Add together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking powder.
Fold flour mixture into pumpkin.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper sprayed with Pam.
Pour mixture over wax paper.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: aunt lyd's punch
directions: Mix gelatin completely in hot water.
Add cold water and fruit juices.
Stir in sugar; chill.
When ready to serve, puree bananas in blender.
Mix fruit juice with ginger ale and pureed bananas. Garnish with fruit slices or ice ring made of strawberries frozen in lemonade.

title: macaroni-hamburger casserole(for electric skillet)
directions: In medium bowl, cut tomatoes into small pieces; add diced celery, pepper and all seasonings.
Set aside.
Preheat frypan to 300°; add vegetable oil and onion; cook until just beginning to brown.
Add meat.
Turn dial to 400°, stirring frequently, until browned.
Remove excess fat, then add tomato mixture.
Stir; bring to boil.
Cover; close vent and reduce heat to medium simmer. Cook for at least 25 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.
Simmer 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugars.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, vanilla and soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Drop from a tablespoon on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spread crackers on top of foil as close together as possible.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Spoon this mixture over crackers.
Put cookie sheet in 400° oven for 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove and pour melted Hershey bars over top.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Chill dough; roll into balls (size of a walnut).
Roll balls in mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft, at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Spread on crackers.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot and simmer for at least 3 hours to allow flavors to mingle. This is a great stew to make anytime of the year. In the summer, you can use fresh veggies and in the winter you can use frozen, canned or dried veggies. Also, you can add corn, green beans, peas etc. to please your family's taste buds.

title: *quince preserves("liko")
directions: Wash eggs and have at room temperature.
Bring a large pot of water to a boil.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour and stir until mixed well.
Put in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, square or round, greased. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brownies will be chewy and moist.

title: marinated cauliflower
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate cauliflower.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Form cream cheese into heat-safe pan.
Dump chili on top. Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Put in 350° oven until melted and bubbly.
Serve hot with chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all three ingredients together well.
Form into small balls and bake at 375° until slightly brown.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well with the exception of the frozen strawberries.
Leave partially frozen and drain 1/2 of juice off the berries.
Add all fruits, then add pie filling to hold salad together.
You may use any type fresh fruits as a substitute.

title: apricot candy
directions: Put apricots and coconut through a food chopper twice.
Add juice and turn onto board sprinkled with sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Pack in pan.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *I put mine in food processor.

title: nacho chili dip
directions: Preheat oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
In 8-inch round glass baking dish, spread soft cream cheese evenly along bottom.
Evenly layer chili on top.
Next, top with shredded cheese.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until chili is bubbling.
Once out of the oven, sprinkle tomatoes and spring onions on top.

title: mom's french chef meat loaf
directions: Fry out the salt pork.
Add onion and cook until golden brown. Add pork and onion to other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes, then decrease heat to moderate (350°) and bake for 30 minutes longer, or until done.
Or, microwave on High for 20- to 25 minutes, or until done.
Serve hot or cold.
This is a very good, juicy meat loaf, not dry.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip; beat well.
Layer wafers in bottom of pan.
Slice bananas on top of wafers.
Layer pudding (1/2 of it).
Repeat wafers, bananas and pudding until all gone.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Add the tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Put sliced potatoes and onions on top. Simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix cooking apples, raisins, nuts and sugar; let stand 1 hour. Stir often.
Mix together flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and soda. After one hour, mix and beat well cooking oil, vanilla and 2 eggs. Add this to apple mixture, then add sifted ingredients to apple mixture.
Beat by hand until well moistened.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Fill about half full or divide mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: mexican pepper bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Grease iron skillet.
Pour half the mixture into skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture, then pour the remaining half over cheese.
Bake in oven at 325° until done.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes uncovered.
To freeze, do not cook first.

title: slow cooker vegetable soup
directions: In a slow cooker, combine first 10 ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 6 hours. Add vegetables. Cover and cook on high 2 more hours or until the meat and vegetables are tender.

title: mom's black walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add black walnuts which have been floured with a little of the flour.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour or a little longer.
Ice with butter icing and decorate with walnuts.

title: tiny apple cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place paper liners in eight (1/3-cup) muffin cups.
Place a cookie in bottom of each; set aside.
In a small skillet, melt butter.
Add apples; cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; spoon over cookies.
With an electric mixer beat cream cheese, egg, sour cream, vanilla and remaining 5 tablespoons sugar until smooth.
Spoon over apples. Bake until set, 25 to 28 minutes.
Cool on a rack; remove cakes.
Cover and refrigerate until cold, about 2 hours.
Garnish with sour cream, apple slices and crushed vanilla wafers.

title: spanish style carrots and celery
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in oil.
Add carrots, celery and seasonings.
Cover with tomato sauce and water.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Prepare chicken breasts. Cook until tender and done. Cut into bite-size pieces. Mix together soup, nuts, salt, pepper, lemon juice, mayonnaise and onion. Mix chicken and celery. Place each mixture in layers in a casserole. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° until baked through. If desired, cheese can be sprinkled on top. Casserole may be prepared day before.

title: parmesan baked cod
directions: Combine flour, corn meal and seasonings.
Melt margarine in shallow baking dish.

title: easy floated bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs to the milk.
Butter slices of bread and arrange in 1 1/2-quart baking dish, buttered side down, with raisins between slices.
Pour liquid mixture over them and let stand for 1 hour.
Dot top with butter; bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve while hot with hard sauce or cream or plain.

title: cheesy baked chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in melted butter then in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat with mixer.
Stir cookie crumbs in and blend well.
Fold coconut and pecans in. Place in a greased cake (tube) pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian beef roast for hot sandwiches ala chicago
directions: Rub Adolph's meat tenderizer into roast.
Moisten with water. Pierce all over with thin metal skewers so tenderizer goes into roast.
Rub a bit of Kitchen Bouquet over roast.

title: memorable macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice.

title: rolls
directions: Mix like biscuits.
Roll out on a board.
Grease pan well. Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400° until brown.

title: easter eggs
directions: Cream together oleo and 1/2 pound of 4xx sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Grease iron skillet and pour in half mixture.
Sprinkle half of shredded cheese.
Pour remaining mixture in; top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cinnamon bread
directions: Combine milk, oats, sugar, salt and oil in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add to oatmeal mix. Add 2 cups flour, beating well.
(Best to use bread attachments on mixer.)
Add remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Either use kneading forks on mixer or turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn out on
floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Round out each half to 15 x 9-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over dough.
Sprinkle with raisins and nuts.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans (Corning or heavy best).
Let rise in warm place until dough fills pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Stir in potato chips.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely; sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: mandarin orange gelatin ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice; stir until melted.
Add ice cream, oranges and crushed pineapple; stir well, but do not use beater.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate and chill overnight to set.
Serves 24.

title: chile corn bread
directions: Put first 7 ingredients together in large bowl, beat about 1 minute until well blended.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place half of mix in pan, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle chopped chiles over batter.
Sprinkle all of cheese over chiles.
Spread rest of batter on top of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in baking pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add water.
Place chicken in single layer on rice.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. (Add water, if necessary, at end.)

title: bruchetta
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Place bread slices on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Drizzle each slice with olive oil.
Bake approximately 8 minutes or until the bread is toasted golden brown.
Remove and cool slices.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add carrots, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Saute beef, rice and onion in oil for 5 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper, broth and 1/4 cup Ragu sauce.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender.
Add salt, vanilla, sugars and butter.
Place in casserole dish and top with pie crust strips (homemade or store bought) in lattice design.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, flour, whipping cream and extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Note:
I use a 5-gallon soup pot because you can freeze this soup.
It's okay to cut this recipe in half.

title: crab cakes
directions: Note:
Bake crabmeat on cookie sheet for 5 minutes at 350°. Any shells will easily be seen and can be removed.

title: apricot pork
directions: Stuff pork loin with your favorite dressing.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Spoon sauce over roast to glaze the last 1/2 hour.
Pass remaining sauce when serving.

title: cherry coconut squares
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup sugar until light; stir in 1/2 cup flour.
Put into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt, vanilla, eggs, nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly over baked dough.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water; cool.
Add milk and mayonnaise; blend both mixtures with mixer.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and horseradish.
Mold and chill for several hours. This is a very delicious tangy, congealed.
(Do not leave out horseradish.)

title: swedish rye bread
