directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. To the scalded milk, add sugars, shortening, salt, molasses, orange peel and orange juice. Cool to lukewarm.

title: banana punch
directions: In large container, mix pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
In a saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Boil for 3 minutes, or until sugar is well dissolved.
Let cool.
Add mashed bananas and sugar water to fruit juice mixture.
Freeze.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Chop the onion and saute in the oleo.
When nearly clear, add the small can of mushrooms and heat thoroughly.
Add the can of roast beef and stir to separate the pieces of beef.
Add the sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Add a tossed salad and rolls for a complete meal.
This recipe will serve 2 people.

title: cheese, basil and tomato casserole
directions: Scatter croutons over bottom of a 9-inch glass pie plate. Overlap alternate slices of tomato and Mozzarella cheese on top in a circular pattern to cover.
Sprinkle with basil, chives and pepper.
Microwave uncovered on High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven, spoon dressing on top.
Let stand 5 minutes for flavors to develop.
Makes 6 servings, 171 calories per serving.

title: french meat pie
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside. Brown beef and pork together. Drain. Combine meat, onion, potatoes and seasoning.
Fill pastry with mixture and top with crust.
Brush top of crust with egg, if desired. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple gift cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until very light.
Add beaten egg. Measure, mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture and stir in apples.
Drop in balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ono oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll pieces in mayonnaise, then roll each piece in the crushed cornflakes.
Bake for one hour in 325° oven or until done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and cook over low heat about 1 minute, stirring well to dissolve sugar.
Add oleo; keep beating to melt.
Do not overbeat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to harden.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend together and allow to sit for at least 2 hours (best overnight).
Will keep for weeks in a closed container in the refrigerator.
Serve with carrot strips.
Other veggies are good also but it is best with carrots.

title: chicken tetrazzini(cooking light)
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion and saute 7 minutes or until liquid evaporates.
Stir in all-purpose flour.
Gradually add chicken broth, skim milk and light process cheese.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 tablespoons Parmesan and next 5 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: apricot syrup
directions: In blender or food processor, puree apricots and juice until smooth.
Combine apricots, syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil gently, still stirring, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 cups.

title: holiday kiwi fruit salad
directions: Dip pear and apple in lemon juice to prevent darkening. Reserve 3 tablespoons of cranberry sauce.
Slice remainder in quarter slices.
Arrange kiwi fruit, cranberry slices, pear and apple on lettuce.

title: grandma mcmahon's chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately, ending with buttermilk.
Melt together butter and chocolate.
Add to mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter. Add onions to soften. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (iron skillet is best). Yummy with beans.

title: california tamale pie
directions: In a medium skillet, brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain fat.
In medium bowl, combine milk, 1 cup of cornmeal and eggs; blend well.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients except cheese and 2 tablespoons of cornmeal.
Stir to blend.
Pour into lightly-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and 2 tablespoons of cornmeal.
Continue baking until cheese melts and cornmeal browns.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
Cool a little; peel and slice.
Add onion.
In large skillet, cook bacon and dice; set aside.
Pour off bacon grease.
Return 1/2 cup grease to skillet.
Add sugar, oleo, salt, pepper, vinegar and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Pour over potato and onion mixture.
Add half of the diced bacon and chopped parsley.
Toss well.
Add rest of bacon.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
(Better on second day.) Makes 10 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Combine all ingredients, except celery.
Chill for 1 hour to blend flavors.
Spread on celery.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix, dry, until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolk. Drizzle over apples.
Topping will not completely cover apples. Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake. Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Cut stack of tortillas into 8 wedges each.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cumin and salt. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until dry and crisp.
Monitor your chips as to not overbrown.
Store in an airtight container. Serve with salsa.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread into 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pineapple rings.
Place cherries in centers on rings.
Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Blend in remaining butter.
Add fruit and buttermilk.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Gradually add buttermilk to mixture, beating until blended. Spread batter over fruit.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool on rack and then serve.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.	Pound all flour possible into steak.
Sear in hot oil.
Add water, tomato juice, and onion. Simmer slowly until done, adding more tomato juice as needed to keep meat covered.	Serve with wild rice.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: In shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper.
In second shallow dish, combine egg and lemon juice; beat until foamy.
In third shallow dish, place crushed Rice Krispies.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Coat chops by dipping in flour mixture, egg/lemon juice mix, then crushed Rice Krispies.
Over medium heat, brown both sides of chops.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
One-third cup mix per cup of hot water.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Pour into
two greased 9-in. 5-in.x3-in. loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60-70 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack; cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Preheat oven
Grease one 8-inch loaf pan.
Beat shortening and sugar until smooth and creamy. Add salt, eggs, bananas, sour cream and baking soda.
Lastly, add the flour. Turn batter into pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove from pan and cool on rack for 1 hour before serving. Stores well in freezer.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add milk to pudding gradually. There is no need to cook this. Just proceed as you usually do to freeze the ice cream in your ice cream freezer. You may add flavoring or different flavored pudding for variation.

title: rice and shrimp
directions: Following directions on package, cook rice in medium saucepan. In large skillet, melt butter.
Add shrimp, diced onion and mushrooms.
Season with garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add prepared rice and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll out biscuits to 3 1/2 to 4-inches in diameter.
Bake over backs of large muffin cups 8 to 9 minutes. Brown meat and drain. Stir in beans, sauce and water.
Heat to boil.
Remove tart cups and fill with meat/bean mixture. Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Marinate tomatoes, broccoli, olives and mushrooms in Italian dressing for 3 hours.
Cook pasta according to package directions. Add cooled pasta to vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.

title: fantastic
directions: This is 4 layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over bottom. Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over bottom.
Mix next 2 ingredients and spread over second layer.
Spread the last of the Cool Whip over the pudding.
Chill overnight.
You can add chopped nuts and a cherry on the top of the Cool Whip.

title: blueberry cup cakes
directions: Mix together egg, sugar, sour cream and oil, then add flour and baking soda.
Stir well and add blueberries.
Bake in cup cake papers or greased muffin tin in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
These blueberries will never fall to bottom.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook onions and celery in oleo.
Add green onions and parsley and cook 15 more minutes.
Add seasoning and tails.
Cook 8 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onions, Jalapenos, and tomatoes. Mix the rest of the ingredients in a blender set on puree until semi chunky. Salsa should be a liquid chunky mixture. Eat with any type of chips.

title: banana boats
directions: Make a lengthwise cut, about 1/2-inch deep, down the top of each unpeeled banana.
Brush each banana with lemon juice.
Divide chocolate pieces and marshmallows evenly among bananas and fill the split in each banana.
Place in individual bowls.
Microwave on High for about 3 minutes or until chocolate melts.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop.
Add sugar and jello.
Stir and cook few more minutes.
Add pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pour off stock (about 4 cups).
Add onion, bay leaves and flat noodles to stock; boil 7 minutes.
Add white raisins and slivered almonds.
Bone chicken and add.
Mix lightly; add salt and pepper.
Put in a greased baking dish; store in refrigerator overnight (if too dry, add broth).
When ready to bake, spread cream of mushroom soup over mixture.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and add pats of butter.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 16 to 20 people.

title: spinach-stuffed shells
directions: Cook macaroni shells according to package directions; drain and set aside.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli in water (overdone).
Saute onion in butter; add cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms and juice.
Break up garlic cheese and add to mixture.
Add hot sauce and broccoli.
Mix well. Keep warm in chafing dish; eat with dipper potato chips.
Can also be used in patty shells or over noodles as a casserole.

title: marshmallow cups
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. With a brush, coat paper cups with chocolate. Chill until firm. Fill with marshmallow creme to 1/8 inch of top. Cover top with melted chocolate. Chill again. Place in airtight container to store.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in greased casserole at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: beef and bean tostada
directions: Deep fry tortillas until golden brown.
Cook hamburger meat until well cooked, then pour onion.
Stir until onion is cooked. Cook chorizo for 20 minutes, then mix it with meat, chorizo and beans.
Spread the ingredients on the tostada.
Garnish with tomatoes, lettuce and onion and sour cream.

title: toffee bark
directions: Chop chocolate into small pieces and melt carefully.
Fold in nuts and toffee bits.
Pour onto a lightly oiled cookie sheet. Let it cool and set up.
Break into pieces. Store in a covered container in a cool place.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (oats, sugar, baking powder and salt). Set aside.
Combine egg, butter and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, let sit just a few minutes and then quickly remove from pan.
A sharp spatula works best.

title: grandma's pretty stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients well!
Chill well and ready to serve.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease only bottom of pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom.
Thoroughly combine thawed strawberries and syrup with Jell-O; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moist; beat on medium 3 minutes.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in pan. Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Seve warm or cool with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream the cream cheese with sugar and milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Fold in angel food cake pieces.
Top with cherries. Refrigerate.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: hot pepper cornbread
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add carrots, potatoes and water.
Bring to boil.
Add Miso, soy sauce, vegetable bouillon and spices, stirring occasionally while adding them.
Turn down to medium heat; cover and let cool 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes about 6 cups of soup.

title: low-fat lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and add spaghetti sauce, water and salt.
Spread 1/3 meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking pan. Lay 1/2 noodles over sauce.
Spread 1/2 cottage cheese over noodles.
Sprinkle 1/3 Mozzarella over cottage cheese.
Repeat. Then top with remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top. Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Cover opposite way (double wrap). Ideally, let set for a few hours.
Cook in microwave at Medium or slightly higher for 30 minutes.
Turn if you don't have turntable every 10 minutes.
Remove plastic wrap.
Add last of Mozzarella. Cook on Medium heat for 2 more minutes.
If you wish, sprinkle with parsley.
Slice and serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water, sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Add tea bags; steep for several minutes.
Add pineapple juice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar (1/2 cup) and margarine until crumbly.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar, milk and cream cheese until smooth, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over crust.
Spread blueberry filling. Chill thoroughly.
Serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add egg and juice.
Mix well.
Add nuts and fruit cocktail.
Pour into pan, 13 x 9 1/2-inch.
Top with brown sugar.
Dot with oleo and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili party wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake wings in bag, a few at a time, until coated.
Place skin-side up in a single layer in well-buttered shallow baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes; turn wings and bake until tender, about 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and pour in all liquid ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: lemon chicken(method:  foil)
directions: Arrange chicken on foil with fruit slices above and below. Wrap and place in coals.
Turn after 10 minutes.
Cook another 10 to 15 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: baked carrots
directions: Scrape or pare carrots and place in casserole. Cream butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon together; add water and blend well.
Pour over carrots; cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple orange slush
directions: Combine pineapple-orange juice and sherbet in blender.
Add ice and blend until slushy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, water and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured board. Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool. Makes 2 1/2 dozen, 2 1/2-inch cookies.
May be decorated.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese together and put in bottom of
1 to 1 1/2 quart dish.
Layer crackers over top. Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak sauce
directions: Put chutney in blender and grind up all fruit.
Put this and remainder in large bowl and mix.
Save all bottles and put steak sauce back into these bottles.

title: fat-free spice cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.
In medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, stir sugar and milk until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add egg whites, corn syrup, and vanilla; stir until blended.
Gradually add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up and cook first 3 ingredients until tender in little water.
Drain well.
Melt 2 sticks margarine; add to this stuffing mix.
Toss until all of margarine is absorbed.
Layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Put squash over and top with small amount of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash and onion casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Note:
You will need a tube pan for baking this cake.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes (9 cubes per slice).
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together until well blended. Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Use tortilla chips to eat with dip.

title: pizza dippers
directions: Brown meat, drain; combine dry ingredients, cut in shortening as in pie crust, then add meat and cold water.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with sauce for dipping.

title: pepperidge farm chicken
directions: Crush stuffing mix until fine.
Wash chicken and dip in margarine and mustard mix, then dip in stuffing.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana-strawberry parfait pie
directions: Heat strawberry juice and water (1 1/4 cups) to boiling point in a 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberry-banana jello and stir until dissolved.
Cut ice cream into pieces and add to hot liquid; stir immediately until melted.
Chill until mixture is thickened, but not set, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Beat at a low speed until fluffy.
Pile lightly into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour. Toss crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Continue baking for 30 minutes uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine oranges, coconut and sugar; mix lightly.
Chill. Serve on lettuce covered platter.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: opal's fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits in a bowl and add Cool Whip to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: judy's chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in oleo until tender.
Add flour until thick.
Add chicken, pimento, black pepper, eggs, soup and mayonnaise; mix.
Then add 1 cup of crushed chips.

title: cold slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Slice onions. Place on top of cabbage. Sprinkle with 2 cups sugar. Put oil, vinegar, dry mustard, celery seed, salt and 4 teaspoons sugar in pan; bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage. Cover with lid or foil to steam. Allow to cool and refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: cranberry iced tea
directions: In large saucepot, combine boiling water and tea bags.
Let stand for 4 minutes.
Remove and discard tea bags.
In large pitcher combine brewed tea, cranberry juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Chill mixture for at least 1 hour or until ready to serve. Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices if desired.
One cup serving contains 116 calories.

title: gluten
directions: Make a stiff dough and cover with water.
Let soak 1 or 2 hours or overnight.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. When cake is done, prick cake with fork while still warm.
Pour pineapple and juice over warm cake.
Blend pudding with milk and beat in cream cheese (small amount at a time).
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and coconut. Refrigerate until serving time.
The longer the cake is refrigerated, the better the flavor.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir until dissolved the water, salt, sugar and yeast, then add slightly beaten eggs and shortening.
First mix with spoon, then with hands; add potatoes and flour.
After mixing thoroughly, place in refrigerator about 2 hours before baking.
Shape into desired shape.
Cover and let rise until light or double in size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen or can be used in smaller quantities and will store about 4 days in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Hand mix meat, onion, garlic salt and pepper, egg and oatmeal. Shape into loaf and place in 9 x 13 inch pan. Top loaf with tomato paste. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until browned.

title: stone keys
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth. Blend in eggs one at a time. Remove 1 cup of batter and spread into bottom of crust; set aside. Add pumpkin, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg to the remaining batter and stir gently until well blended. Carefully spread over the batter in the crust. Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Allow to cool, then refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Cover with whipped cream, if desired.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together 3 times. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients into tomato soup, alternating small amounts, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Last add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Let stand 24 hours before cutting.
Cover with cream cheese icing or caramel icing, whichever you prefer.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine juices and water in bottom part of percolator. Place all other ingredients in basket of percolator. Perk 5 to 10 minutes. This makes a delicious drink for a party or just to serve on cold days at home.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice until, rinse and drain.
Mix ingredients all together and keep chilled.

title: banana cream cheese pie
directions: Combine butter, crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly on bottom and up sides of pie dish.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Line crust with bananas.
Pour filling over. Chill 3 hours before serving.
Top pie with rest of bananas.

title: shoe peg corn salad(serves 12)
directions: Stir all ingredients together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: broiled peaches
directions: Cut peaches in halves and remove seeds; do not peel.
Put 1 teaspoon brown sugar and 1 teaspoon butter on each half.
Broil for about 20 minutes.
Serve as vegetable with steak or fish.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Bring cherries and juice, water and sugar to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients except pie filling 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into plate.
Spoon pie filling evenly over top.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Top with streusel.
Bake until streusel is brown, about 10 minutes longer.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Blend together the cake mix, 2 eggs and softened butter. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the 2 remaining eggs, sugar and softened cream cheese.
Put on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salad dressing.
Toss until well mixed.
Add dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain before serving.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, carrots, celery and ground beef.
Cover with tomato soup and mushroom soup.

title: country style hominy
directions: Fry bacon and onion until bacon is very crisp.
Add water from 1 can of hominy to bacon and continue to cook about 5 minutes. Discard liquid in other can of hominy.
Add both cans of drained hominy to bacon mixture and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: beef cubes with noodles
directions: Mix all soups with beef.
Bake at 300°
for 3 hours.
Serve on cooked and drained noodles.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Fry onion in margarine and add to the noodles.
Add cheese, sour cream and sugar; mix well.
Lastly, add beaten eggs and transfer to a casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker or bread crumbs.
Serve in squares.

title: eggless cake from canada
directions: Put together all ingredients except flour, baking powder and baking soda in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Let cool.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into glass loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: broccoli stuffed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice 1/4 inch from stem end of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seeds.
Place tomatoes in 1-quart baking dish.
Cook broccoli with onion according to package directions; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Fill tomatoes with broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: foil-wrapped dinners
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Run cold water over peas just until broken apart; drain.
Tear off 4 pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil, each 18 x 15 inches.
On center of each piece, place 1 carrot (thinly sliced), 1 potato (cut into quarters) and 1/4 of the meat.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix; spoon over meat.
Top with peas.
Wrap securely in foil; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Garnish with 2 cherry tomatoes, halved. Serves 4.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth. Cool.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, to mixture in saucepan. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and turn out onto lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir shortening until soft.
Add flour mixture and 1 cup milk.
Mix to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Add remaining milk, eggs, chocolate and food coloring.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Bake at 350° in 3 (8-inch) pans for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well, refrigerate and serve with vegetables.

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss lightly and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kentucky corn cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into cupcake paper in large muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: surprise sweet potatoes
directions: Drain apricots, reserving liquid.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange rind.
Blend well.
Gradually add apricot syrup, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 2 minutes.
Add apricots, butter and pecans. Stir until butter is melted.
Halve sweet potatoes and arrange in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover with apricot sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce until mixed.
Toss with vegetables, salt and pepper.
Chill well.
Serve.

title: trawler restaurant crab dip
directions: Cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add grated sharp Cheddar cheese, minced garlic clove, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, horseradish (cream-style) and crab meat, drained well.
Form in ball and refrigerate a few hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: crushworthy meat loaf
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
Cover; let stand on floured surface at room temperature 1 hour.
Reserve 1 tablespoon egg for glaze.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Shape into a 4 x 9-inch loaf.
Place loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Press dough onto bottom of a greased jelly roll pan.
Place loaf in center of dough.
Fold dough ends over loaf.
Tuck ends in to cover entire loaf.
Brush top and sides of loaf with reserved egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: paul varnell's spaghetti
directions: First...you saute the onion, garlic and bell pepper in the bacon drippings, using a large, deep pot or pan.
Add the 2 small tomatoes (cubed) near the end, for just a few moments.
Add the canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste and catsup.
Blend in all seasonings; reduce heat and allow to simmer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Chill, then serve.

title: pizza in a bowl
directions: Cook the macaroni according to the package directions, except omit the salt.
Drain.
Meanwhile, cut half of the pepperoni slices in quarters; set aside.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in pizza sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, pepper, garlic salt and onion salt.
Stir in the cooked macaroni and quartered pepperoni slices.

title: relish
directions: Grind together tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Add salt, let stand 5 hours, then boil 15 minutes and drain.
Boil next 5 ingredients 2 minutes.
Strain.
Add to first mixture with mustard and celery seed.
Bring to boil and jar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice, sugar and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can be frozen and used as a dessert.

title: katrina's chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Place chicken on bottom.
Place broccoli (blanched) on top of chicken.
Blend soup, milk, mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice. Pour on top of broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese. Add bread crumbs (optional).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place wings in baking pan. Peel and grate onion; mix with chili sauce, vinegar, oil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Stir well. Pour over wings and bake about one hour or until done at 375°. Pour off fat and serve while hot.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice together.
Add nuts, coconut and apples.
Add all the rest of the ingredients. Chill 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Form into balls. Let stand until they dry out some.
Melt chocolate chips in saucepan.
Dip balls; set on wax paper to cool.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish or plastic bag.
Pour dressing over chicken. Cover.
Marinate chicken in refrigerator 1 to 8 hours. Drain.
Dip chicken in combined bread crumbs and pecans. Press to coat.
Cook chicken in margarine in large skillet over medium heat, 5 to 6 minutes on each side, until tender.

title: paula's cornish hens
directions: Remove skin off chicken and cut into pieces.
Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add chicken and spices.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add crushed tomatoes and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Add wine, water, bouillon and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook on low for 30 minutes in a covered pot.
Simmer for another 5 minutes and serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, grapes, pineapple and mandarin oranges; toss well.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add to chicken mixture, stirring well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Sprinkle almonds on top.

title: famous rotel cheese dip
directions: To 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, add cheese, which has been melted in a double boiler (for additional thickness, add more cheese).
Mix together.
Serve warm as dip with corn chips, tortilla chips or crackers.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, onion, soup and sour cream. Spread into casserole dish. Melt 1 cup butter and add to crushed Ritz crackers. Mix and spread on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Drain pineapple and oranges.
Measure fruit juice and add enough water to make 2 cups. Add to jello, along with the fruit.
Congeal.

title: barbecue beef(8 to 20 servings)
directions: Brown the roast well with salt and pepper.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over browned meat.
Cover; simmer for 4 or 5 hours at 250°.
Tear meat and simmer one more hour.
Great sandwiches.

title: bread pudding
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add scalded milk and pour on cubed bread in a casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put pudding in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done (could take a little longer or a little less time).

title: hobo stew
directions: You will need a large black pot.

title: party punch
directions: Combine milk and 2 pints of sherbet.
Beat until smooth.
Add chilled and carbonated beverage and stir until blended.
Spoon remaining sherbet on top.
Makes 28 (1/2 scoop) servings.

title: very easy yeast rolls
directions: Measure milk in pan.
Add sugar, salt, oil or butter.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Warm milk mixture to lukewarm.
Then add yeast.
Add enough flour to make a pretty stiff dough.
Grease the top and let rise double in pan for about 1 hour.
Turn out on floured board and work down.
Shape into rolls.
Let raise again.
Grease the tops and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: lotta bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add beans (pour off liquid).
Add condiments and bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
With mixer, beat oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add cool milk.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water, blending well.
Sift dry ingredients together, then sift into pumpkin mixture, stirring to blend.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pans slightly; remove from pans and cool loaves on wire racks.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: huckleberry bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Stir in berries and cinnamon. Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: unusual frozen cake
directions: Add milk (instead of water) to cake mix, using the same amount as box instructs for water.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Do not bake. Cover pan with foil or tight fitting lid and freeze overnight.
The next day, combine brown sugar, cocoa, boiling water and flavoring or vanilla, stir well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take cake from freezer, remove foil and pour cocoa mixture over frozen cake. Immediately bake for one hour or until done.
Cool.
Refrigerate if you like.
Cut into squares.
Remove squares with cake server and place upside-down on plate.
Top with whipped topping.

title: clam chowder
directions: In crock-pot, put butter in first.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add milk to desired consistency (usually I finish filling the crock-pot).
Cook on low all day or on high for 3 hours.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; then add wet ingredients.
Stir well. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yield:
40 to 60 muffins.

title: broccoli chicken and cheese
directions: In a 10-inch skillet on medium-high heat, brown chicken in butter for 10 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and milk. Add broccoli and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to low; cover and cook 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and sage.

title: hershey's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture. Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from sheets. Makes 6 dozen.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl:
cake mix, gelatin, 1/2 cup strawberry juice and oil.
Beat two minutes at high speed.
Add eggs, beat one minute.
Then add 3/4 cup drained strawberries, beat one minute.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: arroz con pollo for 24
directions: Bake chicken, uncooked, for 30 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon in water and add saffron; stir until dissolved.
Stir in onions, bay leaves, parsley and 4 teaspoons salt; heat to boiling.
Remove pans from oven.
Remove chickens.
Drain fat from pans.

title: apples and cabbage salad
directions: Beat egg and sugar; combine with water.
Let come to almost boil.
Combine flour and vinegar and stir well; combine vinegar combination with sugar, egg and water.
Stir continuously until almost clear.
When sauce is clear (sticky), pour over the apples and cabbage already cut and in bowl.

title: crazy potatoes
directions: Boil quartered potatoes until done.
Pour remainder of ingredients over drained potatoes, sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble bread and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Add spices.
Add 1/2 cup salsa.

title: german liver dumplings
directions: Mix together hamburger, liver, rolls, 1 onion, eggs, flour, bread crumbs, marjoram, salt and pepper; mixture will be soft but will shape in broth.
Form balls, big or small, and drop in hot broth.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
They will rise.
Remove when done; saute the second onion in butter and pour over dumplings.
Serve with sauerkraut or mashed potatoes.

title: quick mix for biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients; blend well.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed.
Put in airtight jar or Tupperware bowl.
Store in a cool place.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.
You can use this for any recipe calling for Bisquick.

title: chicken with dressing
directions: Melt oleo and pour over half stuffing in large pan, 13 x 9. Spoon in other ingredients. Top with remaining 1/2 dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: georgia smothered chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Let stand 1 hour.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 500° until brown; reduce heat to 350°.
Add Worcestershire sauce and water.
Cover tightly with foil. Continue baking 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Gravy may be thickened, if desired.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour, then add milk and egg yellows. Stir and cook on low heat until thick.
After the mixture has thickened, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: mesquite turkey
directions: Place wet mesquite wood chips in 1 disposable aluminum pie pan on coals on one side of the bottom of outdoor grill (remove grids so that pan is sitting directly on the coals).
Very important to keep wood chips wet at all times so it smokes.
Quarter onion and carrots; place in cavity of turkey.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash in the cavity also.
Put turkey in oblong pan on top of grill to one side.
Turn both burners on high for 3/4 hour.
The burner under the larger part of turkey turn low and the other burner turn medium for 4 hours or until done.
This is the turkey that is served at the Leeds' Thanksgiving dinner.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Cook cabbage, celery and carrots in water with bouillon cubes. Add tomato juice and string beans.
Fry hamburger, salt, pepper, onion and parsley.
Add all together and cook slowly.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 tsp. baking soda.
Pour over 6 quarts popped popcorn.
Stir until well mixed. place in a 200 degree oven for 1 hour; stirring at 15 minute intervals.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Store in covered container.

title: banana fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except the vanilla and nuts.
In a heavy saucepan, cook, stirring constantly over moderate heat until it makes the soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until it becomes thick and glossy.
Pour in a buttered 8-inch pan.
Let firm, then cut into squares.

title: pizza dough
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Allow yeast to proof 10 minutes or until it's foamy.
Add remaining 1 cup warm water, combining well with yeast.
Add 3 cups flour and salt.
Mix dough. Add remaining flour as needed to make a dough that holds together.
Place dough on floured surface and knead for 10 minutes or until dough is soft and not sticky.
Grease a large bowl with the olive oil.
Put dough in bowl and turn a few times to coat with oil.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and let rise for 2 hours in warm place.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Beat eggs with 1 cup of sugar.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add apples and nuts. Put in 9-inch greased pie plate.
Add topping (cinnamon and sugar combination).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes approximately.
Has coffee cake texture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Separate the cabbage leaves.
Stuff each leaf with about 2 tablespoons of the mixture.
Pour the tomato sauce over the stuffed leaves.
Cover and cook on low heat about 3 1/2 hours.

title: marie's chicken
directions: Combine preserves, salad dressing and soup mix.
Place chicken pieces in baking pan; spread sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or grill chicken over medium coals until nearly tender, about 45 minutes; turn occasionally.
Brush with sauce, grill 15 minutes more basting occasionally.
Makes 12 servings.

title: seed mounds
directions: Boil honey and salt until a drop forms in cold water.
Add nuts; drop by tablespoons onto platter.
Makes 25.

title: hazel's miracle whip cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt, then add Miracle Whip, coffee and vanilla.
Stir together and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 layers or 1 square pan.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Bisquick.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes. Beat eggs in medium bowl with a fork.
Mix in sugar and almond extract.
Stir in coconut, almonds and 3 tablespoons Bisquick; spread over baked layer.
Arrange cherries on top.
Bake until light golden brown and set at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes; cool. Cut into bars.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle to 350°.
Whisk all dry ingredients together before mixing in liquid ingredients.
Whisk eggs, buttermilk and melted butter into dry mixture.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not whisk until smooth.
Use a 1/2 cup measuring cup to pour onto griddle.
Turn when surface appears bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together, and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter and let cool.
Cream sugar; add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Beat all together.
Add flour and salt.
Add chopped dates, coconut, nuts and candy.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 2 1/2 hours.
Frost.

title: snyder's hobo lasagne
directions: Break spaghetti in 1/2 and cook in boiling water until done, drain.
Brown hamburger, drain grease. Drain mushrooms, add to hamburger.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan; layer with sauce, hamburger, spaghetti and cheese, continue through ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until cheese is melted through.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Place wild rice in strainer.
Pour 3 quarts boiling water over rice 4 times, letting rice set in strainer each time, while water returns to boiling.
Brown onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hour.
Add broth if mixture becomes dry.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: apple spice syrup
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, allspice and nutmeg; mix well.
Add juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until syrup is bubbly and slightly thickened.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan (don't drain pineapple).
Sprinkle coconut over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over coconut.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt butter and pour over nuts.
(Don't mix.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit ripple cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except pie filling.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with pie filling.
Spread remaining batter over fruit, covering as much of the filling as possible.
Swirls in batter and uncovered fruit peeking through are to be expected.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: rich egg batter bread
directions: Place aluminum foil under the napkin in your roll basket and the rolls will stay hot longer.

title: avocado salad with ginger
directions: Combine lemon juice and ginger and salt in small bowl.
Add avocado and toss gently but thoroughly.
Let salad marinate at room temperature for at least 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party mix
directions: In a small bowl, add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour cereal, nuts and pretzels into large Glad-lock zipper bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside zipper bag.
Seal top of bag securely. Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper and cool. Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: cream-cheese corn
directions: Cook corn as directed.
Drain off 3/4 of the water after corn is cooked, then add cream cheese; blend well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until tender; remove from heat. Let cool, peel and slice.
Heat milk and pour 1/2 cup warm milk in flour to thicken sauce.
Add 1 1/2 cups of hot milk, cheese and butter.
Add sliced potatoes, fresh cut onions and sauce.
Repeat until all is used up.
Heat in oven for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Put into ungreased dish and top with 1 roll package Ritz crackers crumbled and sauteed in 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes at 250°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon in deep hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: aunt nellie's applesauce cake
directions: Use "dead ripe" persimmons and put through a strainer.

Sift together all dry ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients. Place in dessert mold and cover with greased or waxed paper and then in kettle with sufficient water, cover tightly and steam for 1 to 3 hours.
(Or place pudding in top pan of double boiler, cover with aluminum foil, then the lid and steam for 1 1/2 hours.)

title: hot baked potato salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in shallow baking dish. Over the top, scatter 6 slices of bacon in pieces and some sliced olives. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Saute onion, beef and celery in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar and spices.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Add to hot dogs.
Sauce may be frozen.

title: texas bean bake
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand about 30 minutes. Cream oleo and both sugars and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with others, then add oats to mixture and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Add topping.

title: chip chop stew
directions: Salt and pepper a cut up chicken.
Brown in oil until cooked. Drain off excess oil.
In the same skillet, add chopped garlic and onion.

title: peanut butter 'n nana sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread.
On ther other one, slice up part of the banana to cover up the bread.
Put together and eat.
"Num Num," says Cale and Kayla.

title: overnight candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and sugar until very stiff.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Turn oven off.
Place in oven and leave overnight.
Remove with spatula.

title: green dip
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.
Is a great raw vegetable dip.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon container.
Keep airtight.
Put 3 tablespoons of mix in 1 cup hot water.
Stir.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream oleo, brown sugar and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients, then oats and chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pecan creamed cheese pie
directions: Note:
Egg Beaters can be used instead of eggs.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat or stir until smooth.
Pour into deep pie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and shortening.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Toss 1/2 cup of chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fresh apple cake(diabetic)
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Add butter, vanilla, egg and sweetener; beat until well blended.
Stir in grated apples and nuts.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes 9 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Soften butter.
Cream with sugar and eggs.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
I usually use a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Wonderful served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into large salad bowl. Crisp the bean sprouts by placing in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Add noodles, sprouts, water chestnuts and chopped eggs. Crumble bacon over all. Add desired amounts of dressing just before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, sugar and salt. Cut in lard. Beat egg. Add vinegar and water. Sprinkle over flour mixture. Blend with a fork. Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan and add the 1/2 cup ground pecans.
In a mixer, beat the remaining ingredients for 2 minutes. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: persian eggplant stew
directions: Peel eggplant and cut lengthwise in 1/2-inch slices.
Sprinkle both sides of each slice lightly with salt (to prevent eggplants from soaking up too much oil while browning).
Set aside.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil.
Blend in the oil, 1/4 cup at a time.

title: aunt esta's chocolate pie
directions: Set eggs and butter out to reach room temperature.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla; add flour and cocoa. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° until set.

title: golden chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan.

title: pressure cooker stew
directions: Brown meat, seasonings and onion in about 1 or 2 tablespoons Crisco.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Add in this order (do not stir): potatoes, carrots, green beans with liquid and tomatoes with the liquid.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure for 18 minutes.
Run water over cooker to lower pressure.
Stir and serve at once.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Combine both mixtures, mixing well.
Stir in nuts.
Form dough into a roll.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruited sweet potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable casserole, combine potatoes with the water.

Cover and microwave on High 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well to combine. Cover and microwave on High 3 minutes or until apple is tender-crisp.
Yields 4 servings.

title: o.k.'s linguini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pepperoni and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Add pepperoni and cheese before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: "applewoods" rolls
directions: Heat milk to 90°; add sugar and yeast.
Mix then add eggs, oil, salt and bread flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Divide into 24 balls.
Cut each ball into 3 pieces.
Put in oiled muffin pan.
Let this rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: super cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth and pour into graham crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
While baking, mix sour cream, vanilla and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Remove pie and pour over top. Bake 5 more minutes; chill.

title: shrimp piau
directions: Fry meat crisp, then fry onions in grease.
Leave all grease and onions, then stir in shrimp and cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; let simmer about 10 more minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew the chicken until done.
Pick off the bones.
Soak tortillas
in
chicken
stock.
Line
baking
dish:
tortilla, chicken, chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Sprinkle garlic salt and chili powder over
the chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together over hot water.
Cool. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar and then chocolate mixture.
Blend.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bone.
Mix soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and sage.
In casserole dish, layer cream sauce mixture, then chicken.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on each layer. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Use no metal utensils!
Do not refrigerate starter.
A 3 pound margarine container will hold 5 cups of starter.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, and bell pepper.
Cover with salt.
Make a syrup of vinegar,
sugar, water, and celery seed.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over cabbage.
Stir and pack. Keeps indefinitely in the freezer.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order and freeze in 8 x 8-inch dish. Thaw before serving.
Can be refrozen.
Keeps well.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour a little batter into a funnel over hot oil.
Fry until brown; sprinkle powdered sugar over each cake and serve.

title: margarita's pasta primavera(low calorie)
directions: Drain any liquid off of cottage cheese.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese and lemon juice.
Set aside.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Combine all wet ingredients including cocoa, then add dry ingredients.
Batter will be very wet.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Be sure center of cake is not wet when toothpick inserted.

title: quick and easy banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and sprinkle
with
flour.
Bake
at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine beaten
eggs,
cream,
salt
and pepper to form
batter.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in batter, then
in
flour
(or crumbled corn flakes).
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Spray
cookie sheet with Pam or cover with oil. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Turn once so can brown on both sides.

title: microwave corn muffins
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add egg, milk and oil and stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 8 (6 ounce) custard cups lined with cupcake papers.

title: squash delight
directions: Mix and drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Fry until brown. Remove from fryer and drain.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients but chicken in a bowl.
Put cut up chicken in casserole and pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Shape into round balls about 1-inch.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate kiss on each cookie by pressing down.
Return to oven for a minute or two.

title: french onion soup(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Separate onions into rings and cook in melted butter until glossy.
Add consomme, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt or cube and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: doughnuts(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients in a bowl. Blend on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add remaining flour. Roll dough out to 3/8 inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
With wide spatula, slide doughnuts into oil.
Turn as they rise to the surface.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes at 375° until golden brown.
Remove and drain.
Do not prick surface!
Let cool and serve.

title: cool and simple citrus pie
directions: Place concentrate in a large mixing bowl and beat about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in whipped topping and add food coloring (if desired), whipping until smooth. Freeze if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into a pie crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: fettuccine alfredo with noodles
directions: In a skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter over low heat; add cream, the cognac and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add morels; simmer and cover them for 10 minutes, keeping mixture warm.
Prepare noodles; drain the pasta and toss it with the butter.
Add the morel mixture and 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove chicken from bone.
Tear it into small pieces.
Mix dressing mix with the water and margarine. In a separate bowl, mix the 2 cans of soup.
Put 1 layer chicken, 1 layer dressing mix and 1 layer soup.
Repeat 3 times (if needed).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and seasonings.
Add tomato paste, sauce and water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
This will be a thin mixture.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spoon about 1 1/2 cups sauce, making a layer across the bottom of the pan, next layer of noodles (uncooked).
Fill in any empty spaces with broken noodles, then sprinkle 1/3 of grated cheese over sauce.
Make 3 layers of sauce, noodles and cheese on top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: abington crumb cake
directions: Grease and flour 11 x 2 1/2 x 7-inch pans.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs; beat lightly.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Blend in with additions of the milk.
Pour into prepared pans and sprinkle with Crumbs.

title: sour cream and chive noodles
directions: Cook
egg
noodles
according
to
package
directions; drain. Combine cottage cheese,
sour
cream, chives, salt and pepper. Pour over egg noodles
and stir to coat evenly.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can add additional sour cream to moisten.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, chipped beef, horseradish and 1/2 of the chopped nuts.
Form into ball and roll in the remaining nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: This delicate sweet dessert is famous at Mexican weddings or other festivities.
A surprising treat for people who think Mexican food is always hot and spicy.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove and chop.
Add vegetables, except for tomatoes, to bacon drippings in pan and saute.
Pour contents of pan (drippings and all) into Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes, peas and bacon and heat well.
Serve hot.

title: chicken log
directions: Beat cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder together. Blend in chicken and celery plus 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Shape into a 9-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Toss together remaining parsley and nuts.
Coat the log.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream and blend together the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop the batter from a teaspoon onto a cookie sheet, leaving lots of room in between cookies.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until the cookies are as brown as you wish.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is gone.
Set aside. Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add cooked raisins.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add chopped prunes and stir in sour cream. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and spices and add to creamed mixture. Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased pans or a flat pan. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 20 minutes or until done. Frost with Creamy Icing.

title: topoppo salad
directions: Mix mashed avocados and packaged guacamole dip seasoning according to package directions.
Mix oil and vinegar (half and half).
Layer the following on a dinner plate for each serving: tortilla chips, refried beans, guacamole, lettuce, peas, onion, tomato, green pepper, chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with oil and vinegar dressing and top with salsa.

title: scallops with shake 'n bake
directions: Bread scallops in Shake 'N Bake.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package (about 20 minutes).

title: hot crab and cheese dip
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix everything (very thick).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until it is bubbly and brown at edges. Serve hot.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients at medium speed; beat about 4 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Pound pan on counter a few times to get air out.
Bake 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes. Turn out and finish cooling.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into slices and freeze, if you want.

title: rivvel soup
directions: Combine the flour, salt and beaten egg.
Mix together with the fingers until mixture is crumbly.
Drop these rivvels into the broth.
Add corn and simmer for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: cherry-chocolate cake and chocolate frosting
directions: Prepare cake according to box directions; add pie filling and bake according to box directions.

title: easy cheese souffle
directions: Whip eggs, milk, mustard and salt in blender.
Butter rectangular Pyrex dish.
Lay 8 to 9 slices of bread in bottom. (Fill in any empty spaces with bread so cheese will not contact dish.)
Cover with 1/2 of the cheese.
Lay 8 or 9 more slices of bread on top and spread remaining cheese over.
Pour liquid mix over.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Can be frozen. Bake 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
Serve immediately.

title: walnut chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix together 1 tablespoon oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Stir into mixture to coat. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup peanut butter and corn syrup in bowl.
Mix well.
Add cereal.
Stir until coated.
Press into pie plate. Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and remaining 1 cup peanut butter.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie plate.
Freeze.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Butter a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Put pecans and coconut in pan and pour cake over them.
Melt and mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix and bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour. (Very important secret of good cookies.)
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars together.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture and mix well.
Blend in egg mixture, oatmeal and nuts.
Dough should be stiff.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, heat vegetable oil.
Cook beef until done. Add mushrooms and broccoli.
Saute with beef for 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
In small bowl, combine soy sauce, lemon juice and cornstarch until smooth.
Add this mixture to beef-vegetable mixture.
Cook on medium heat until thickened. Fold in pimento.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Roll bread to half its thickness. Spread with mayonnaise and Bleu cheese, mixed. Roll asparagus up, jelly roll fashion. Dip in melted butter and place seam side down in pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp and brown. Cut into thirds.

title: chicken-pineapple stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve syrup); set aside.
Pour water over walnuts; drain.
Heat oil in skillet and stir-fry nuts until brown.
Remove.
Stir-fry chicken, garlic, onion and ginger until chicken turns white.
Remove.
Add broccoli; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Return nuts and chicken mixture.
Add pineapple. Combine reserved syrup, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serve on rice.

title: pilaf stuffed chicken
directions: Fry onion in 1/4 cup butter in saucepan until transparent.
Add pine nuts and rice.
Saute until light brown.
Add currants, 1 tablespoon salt and water and a dash of pepper.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until all the water is absorbed.
Add melted butter.
Cool before using as a stuffing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Spoon on topping and refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:
pineapple, cherry pie filling, coconut, nuts.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Stir together in mixing bowl the rolled oats, boiling water, shortening, molasses and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine, stirring to dissolve, the yeast and 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir into lukewarm oatmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix thoroughly; cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Place dough in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and pat into loaf shape.
Let rise in warm place until double (1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rum punch
directions: In punch bowl, place rum, pineapple juice, lemonade and orange juice.
Let steep 1 hour.
Before serving, add ginger ale. Decorate top with fruit slices.

title: upside down pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in heavy skillet and simmer a few minutes.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, fruit juice, salt and baking powder.
Place pineapple rings in skillet.
Place cherries in center of each pineapple ring.
Pour cake batter over all.
Place skillet in preheated 350° oven and bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Flip over onto large cake plate immediately out of oven.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Choose to desired taste all or some of the following vegetables:
cauliflower, broccoli, tomatoes, radishes, onions, celery, peppers, etc.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Stuffing:
Roll or grind 16 round old fashioned "common" crackers into fine crumbs.
Put in good sized bowl adding 1 can minced clams with the juice.
Season with salt and pepper and moisten to proper consistency with sherry.
Use a shallow pan covered with aluminum foil.
Place the shrimp on the pan and with a spoon put stuffing on top of each shrimp.
Bake at 450° to 500° oven for about 15 minutes.
To preserve moisture, place a large lettuce leaf over the dressing.

title: angel cake
directions: Break cake in small bite size pieces.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well.
Add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and then fold in cake pieces.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish and press lightly.
Cover with cherry pie filling or filling of choice.

title: warm bean salad(party size recipe)
directions: Brown sausage, onion and celery.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer until blended.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and serve.

title: crab salad
directions: Shred crab and mix with mayonnaise and celery; chill.
Serves 6.

title: jean's lasagne
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain off grease.
Stir in onion soup, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cook lasagna noodles.
Drain and let stand in cold water.
In a 2-quart oblong dish, place half the meat sauce, then layer noodles and top with a layer of cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until cheese is desired brownness.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Take graham cracker crust and spread peanut butter from 1/2 to 1-inch thick, according to your liking for peanut butter.
Mix pudding per directions on box.
Pour over peanut butter. Chill in the refrigerator 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: cow flops
directions: In saucepan combine first four ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce to medium heat for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Mix in coconut and oatmeal and drop quickly from teaspoon on wax paper or tray and let cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain all excess fat off meat.
Pour in barbecue sauce and let simmer.
Place biscuits into muffin tins. Spread out biscuit dough to cover muffin tin.
Place meat sauce (approximately 2 large tablespoonfuls) into biscuit dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Place grated cheese on top of cups and place back into oven until cheese is melted.

title: aunt lizzy's ice cream dream pie
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gringo chili
directions: In a
large,
heavy
saucepan,
brown chicken and pork. Remove and
set aside.
Add shallots, onions and garlic to pan and saute until tender.
Stir in tomatillos, tomatoes, chicken broth, chiles,
spices,
chicken and pork.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve
in bowls and top with cheese.
Good with either flour or corn tortillas.

title: quick turkey appetizers
directions: Place tortillas on 2 large (9 x 13-inch) baking sheets. Lightly brush both sides of tortillas with oil.
Bake tortillas at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven.
Evenly spread salsa over all tortillas.
Sprinkle turkey, tomato, cilantro, red pepper, olives and cheese evenly over salsa on each tortilla.
Bake tortillas 12 minutes, rearranging baking sheets halfway through. To serve, slice tortillas in eighths.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix powdered sugar and butter.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency.
Frosts a 13 x 9-inch cake or fills and frosts two 8 x 9-inch cake layers.

title: low sugar mocha nut cake
directions: Combine the hot water and coffee; set aside.
Cream the margarine, brown sugar and sweetener with mixer on medium speed, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix for 1 minute.
Stir together flour, cocoa, dry milk, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with coffee and nuts.
Spray a 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking oil; spread batter evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good cake for diabetics.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and then add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer.
Cook lasagna as directed.
Drain.
On pan, spread 1 cup sauce then alternate layers of lasagna, meat, cheese, meat and lasagna, etc., ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until tender, not soft.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: *One-half cup (1/2 cup) unpopped corn equals 3 cups popped.

title: mother's baked beans
directions: Cover beans and baking soda with water and boil for about 2 hours.
Add mustard, sugar, pepper and salt.
Slice one small piece salt pork to the rind and place in center of the beans which have been placed in a 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours until soft.
Add water from time to time to prevent drying out.

title: busy day goulash
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Add salt and pepper, then set aside.
While meat is browning, add macaroni to boiling water and cook until tender; drain.
Add salt and butter. Add tomatoes to meat mixture; bring to simmer.
When bubbling, add macaroni, then simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with toasted French bread and salad.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Melt cranberry sauce over medium heat.
Drain, reserving liquid and berries.
Mix cranberry liquid, boiling water and gelatin; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly on spoon.
Add mayonnaise and mix until smooth.
Fold in cranberries, apple and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cook bell pepper and onion with 2 tablespoons water in microwave for 2 minutes, or saute for 5 minutes in small amount of oil.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and rest of ingredients to meat. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
As soon as it comes from the oven, put 1/2 cup Arby's sauce or any seasoned catsup on top.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Rinse with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine lemon juice, vinegar and sugar in large pot and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and add green peppers and boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in Certo and food coloring if desired.
Place in hot jars.
If you wish to strain the bits of peppers from the juice, do so before adding the Certo.
Also, if you like hot sauces, blend or chop 6 to 8 hot peppers with the green peppers. Delicious with cream cheese or meats.

title: fish milanese
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper and onion.
Rinse fish and pat dry.
Place fish in marinade, coat well.
Cover and refrigerate.
In one hour turn fish over.
Leave in refrigerator for 1 more hour.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip fish in egg mixture, coat with flour and then bread crumbs firmly around fish.
Refrigerate for about 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet.
Melt 1/4 cup butter, add garlic and cook until light brown.
Add parsley and pour over fish.
Serve with lemon wedge.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chili spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2 sprayed pan.
Cover.

title: hot brown
directions: Combine yellow cheese, 1/2 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce with white sauce and stir over low heat until cheese melts. Place a slice of turkey on each slice of toast and cover with cheese sauce.
Place 2 strips of bacon on each sandwich and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Place on pan and bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: boiled chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand for 1/2 hour until cool (if you can).

title: zebras
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Line with foil.
Grease foil.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring often.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Mix flour and baking powder.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together to resemble crumbs.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Knead gently 20 strokes.
Bake at 450° for 10-20 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip or beat with electric mixer 5 minutes.
Place in refrigerator a few hours.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Place butter into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add squash, salt and pepper.
Combine beaten egg, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion, pimento and sugar.
Pour over squash.
Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potatoes deluxe
