directions: Peel cooled potatoes and grate.
Add rest of ingredients to potatoes.
Bake in a covered casserole for 45 minutes at 375°.
If you prefer, put them in a slow cooker for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms with margarine in saucepan; salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: christmas brunch jam
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Chop cherries in blender.
Combine pineapple, juice, cherries and sugar in large nonaluminum Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Bring to full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring.
Stir in pectin.
Boil 1 minute more. Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Ladle into hot sterilized jars.
Leave 1/4-inch space in top of jar.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
(Put in a boiler of water and bring them to a boil and let them boil for 10 minutes.)

title: grape conserve
directions: Wash grapes.
Separate skins from grapes and pulp.
For every six quarts of grape pulp, add 2 cups of cold water and boil them until the seeds are all loosened out.
Then run them through a Folely food mill, then put the seedless pulp back in a large dish with the skins.
Stir.
Measure all this by the cup (as you put it in both pulp and skins).
To 3 cups of grape mixture, add 1 full cup of sugar and cook slowly for hours until real thick.
When it is nearly done, taste for sweetness, as more sugar may be added.

title: spritz
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Work in the flour.
Using 1/4 of the dough at a time, force dough through cookie press onto ungreased baking sheet in desired shapes.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set but not brown. Cookies may be decorated with colored sugar or cherries before baking.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and drain. Combine all ingredients and either bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven or cook in a crock-pot overnight. Add shredded cheese immediately after cooking cycle.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into baking pan and bake for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve with crackers.

title: hilda's pot roast
directions: Brown roast in heavy pot.
Brown all sides, using no fat. Next, season with salt and garlic powder.
Cover and cook on low heat for 2 hours; do not add water!
Remove roast from pan; cover. Add water to gravy mix as per directions.
Add to pan gravy. Cook until thickened.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Slice roast and return to pan to reheat.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring vegetables to boil and cook until done.
Meanwhile, make thickening.
Cook melted butter and flour until bubbly.
Stir into soup and add cream and cheese.

title: caramel ice cream topping
directions: Heat stove to 100° or low setting.
Put 1 cup sugar in saucepan.
Stir until sugar clumps and turns very brown.
Then pour 1 cup of water in pan with sugar. Keep stirring constantly until like syrup.
Pour over ice cream.
Very gooood.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain paper towel.
Save 1/4 cup drippings from bacon in skillet.
In medium bowl, tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon and with onion slices, tossing until well mixed.
Stir remaining ingredients over medium heat to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add lettuce mixture, tossing until lettuce is slightly wilted and coated with dressing.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees until done, approximately 45 min.

title: carrots in orange sauce
directions: Wash and pare carrots.
Cut into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Mix together all ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pork tandori
directions: Combine first nine ingredients.
Pour over meat that has been well pierced.
Leave 6 to 8 hours or more refrigerated.
Remove bay leaves and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours, basting frequently.

title: baked spinach
directions: Combine spinach, egg, milk and cracker crumbs. Add seasoning and place in a buttered baking dish.
Combine remaining crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Take off burner and add peanut butter, cocoa, vanilla and oats.
Spoon onto wax paper.
When cooled, store in Tupperware to keep fresh.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, flour, milk and butter. Bring to a hard boil; boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: mama's honey wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir to melt shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Add softened yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.

title: pecan praline sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add pecans. Cook and stir until light brown; add sugar and syrup.
Continue to stir until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoon of mixture into each cup.
Bake according to directions on cake mix.
Don't undercook.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and margarine until smooth. Using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, bake on hot griddle. Stir in a little more buttermilk if batter becomes thick.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: chicken dinner bars
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine.
Combine with Rice Krispies and pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat together sugar and syrup (do not boil).
Add peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture.

title: mom crews coconut refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and blend.
Combine soda and salt with flour, then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and coconut, mixing thoroughly after each ingredient.
Divide dough into 3 balls, then shape into rolls and roll in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into slices with a sharp knife.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter stove top cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a full boil.
Boil two minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Add nuts or coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: green enchilada sauce
directions: Wash tomatoes; quarter and remove all seeds.
Peel garlic.
Put all ingredients in large pot with a quart of water.
Watch pot so tomatoes won't stick.
Add water as needed.
When all tomatoes are tender, take off stove and cool.
Run everything through blender. Return to stove; bring to a boil.
Put in quart jars and process 45 minutes.
Makes 7 to 9 quarts.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer chicken.
Combine next three ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: gelatin jiggles
directions: Combine unflavored gelatin and jello.
Add boiling water. Stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares or use cookie cutters to make shapes.

title: moravian love feast buns(butter semmels)
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Stir in the mashed potato and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cover; let stand in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add the milk to the butter and stir until melted. Cool.
Mix in the eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Add the flour gradually, stirring in enough to form a soft dough.
Knead dough on a floured surface until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl; grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough and divide into two portions.
Roll out one portion of dough into a 12-inch square 1/4-inch thick; brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Cut dough into 2-inch squares.
Turn up the corners together.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushrooms and cheese.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) until rice is tender and water absorbed.
Stir in mushrooms and sprinkle with cheese. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash peppers and cut open; clean out seeds.
Cook hamburger; season with salt and garlic.
Drain and fill peppers with hamburger meat and cheese.
Cook at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Peel and core apples. Cut into quarters and roll each quarter in a crescent roll. Put into baking dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over rolls. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Warm milk.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with milk into egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Cover batter with apple slices, slanted upright. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen fluffy strawberry pie
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, combine coconut with melted margarine or butter.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of pie plate.

title: prize winning broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Pour melted margarine over cheese.
Spread stuffing on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, flour, egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff.
Mix corn batter with egg whites and fry in oil until brown and flip.

title: bean and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain and put in a large pan.
Drain the kidney beans and add to macaroni.
Drain the stewed tomatoes and cut into smaller pieces.
Add the tomatoes and tomato sauce to the pan. Cut the hot dogs into bite-size pieces and brown in a separate pan sprayed with a cooking spray.
Add to mixture.
Stir all ingredients together and simmer until hot. Serves 2 to 3.
Goes well with a salad or cole slaw.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut(friska kiselo zelje)
directions: If the sauerkraut is too sour, it should be rinsed in clean, cold water; drain.
Place sauerkraut in a kettle to cook.
Add washed spareribs.
Cook together, adding hot water.
When meat is tender, make brown sauce.
Add a little chopped onion and brown together.
Pour into the cooking sauerkraut and spareribs.
Boil a short time together.
Remove from heat and serve hot with polenta or mashed potatoes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes until partially done.
Put cream cheese, cream of celery soup and milk in a pan and warm until mixed through.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dijon honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and process until smooth.
Serve over salad greens, etc.

title: company stew
directions: Mix and pour soups, water, wine and mushrooms over lightly floured and browned stew meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Fold in sour cream and serve.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Chill until mixture mounds.
Pour into 8 1/2-cup lightly-oiled mold or pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Coat rhubarb with mixture of white sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Place in baking dish.
Top with a mixture of the butter, 1 cup flour and the brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Fry sausage until brown. Don't drain grease, just add flour until sausage is coated with flour. Then add milk, salt and pepper. Cook on medium heat until bubbly. Serve with biscuits.

title: sugar ridge farm scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased 3-quart casserole, place a layer of thin sliced potatoes, some ham, handfuls of onions, cheese, peas and a sprinkling of salt and pepper.
Dust with flour and re-layer potatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
Lay a few chunks of margarine on top.
Fill casserole with milk until about 2 inches from top.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) for 2 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Cut up beef and onions (stems and all).
Mix everything together.
Form a ball.
Roll ball in ground nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: mulled cider
directions: Heat covered but do not boil.
Hold over very low heat 15 minutes to allow flavors to develop.

title: grapefruit fizz
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and spices. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Strain. Combine with grapefruit juice, lime juice and ginger ale. Pour over ice cubes and garnish with lime slices. Very refreshing!

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and let come to room temperature.
Cream cheese and butter until well blended.
Add other ingredients.
Use a cookie press with a star-shaped disk to shape dough into long rows on cookie sheet.
With a knife, cut across rows to make individual straws.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: henrietta's butter cookies
directions: Dip apple slices in batter and deep fry in hot oil.
I sometimes dip the slices in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon before dipping them in batter.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and spices; blend well.
Stir in flour, applesauce and baking soda; beat well.
Add raisins.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to 238° (cook to 240° if weather is damp) to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (110°), about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Requires very little beating.
Quickly stir in walnuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli salad #1
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli mixture just before serving.

title: spiced pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into bite size pieces and spread on cookie sheet.
Pour oil over the pretzels.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and sprinkle over the pretzels.
Toss together.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: texas cowboy goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Set aside.
Brown ground hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in chili powder.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn and stir.
Pour all into macaroni and cheese. Mix well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: old fashioned bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Drain and place in large soup kettle. Add ham bone and 3 quarts of water. Simmer slowly for an hour. Stir in mashed potatoes and let simmer another hour. Then add all the remaining ingredients and simmer another hour or until done. Remove the ham bone; dice the meat off of it and return the meat to the kettle. Discard the bone. Serve with corn bread or large chunks of warm French bread.

title: chicken rotel spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Save 1 1/2 cups of broth and cook spaghetti in chicken broth; do not drain. Dice chicken into bite size pieces. Dice cheese and add to hot spaghetti. Stir until cheese is melted. Saute onion in butter. Add all ingredients. Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix ginger with half the flour and coat pork.
Heat oil in large frying pan; brown coated pork and remove from pan.
Drain pineapple and reserve syrup.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 2/3 cup.
(If not using pineapple, use 2/3 cup water.)
Stir liquid into remaining flour.
Add liquid mixture, vinegar and 2 tablespoons soy sauce to fat in frying pan.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add sugar, pepper and pork.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour over low heat.
Add pineapple and green pepper and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: florence's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs (unbeaten), sour cream, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix turkey and poultry seasoning.
Add egg, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.

title: gas grilled chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken. Do not cut up. Salt to taste, cover with foil. Before closing foil, pour in the cup of water. Close foil.
Place on grill and cook with hood down for 1 hour at 350 degrees. Uncover and brush on sauce. Cook uncovered for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: nanimo bars
directions: In double boiler, cook first 5 ingredients until thick.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and walnuts.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Cream butter, pudding, sugar and flavoring.
Spread over first mixture and chill.
Melt chocolate and butter; spread over top.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meats and drain off fat.
Add
cheese and spices and stir until melted.
Toast bread with a little margarine on each piece.
Spread a small amount of meat mixture on each piece of toasted
bread and place in warm oven until ready to serve.
This is a great little appetizer and recipe freezes well.

title: apple joy cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and mix until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Continue to beat.
Add oil gradually.
When all mixed, add apples, nuts and flavoring. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Saute onions until tender, adding hamburg to keep moist. Flavor with parsley, oregano and basil.
Set aside when browned, and pour off fat.
Boil potatoes in tomato juice and add corn with juice when tender.
Combine all ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut in shortening with dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix until ball forms. Do not knead.
Pat out onto a floured board and cut with a large cutter.
Bake in a 500° oven for 10 minutes. Makes 20 to 25 biscuits.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter until blended.
Beat the eggs and sugar together.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 25 minutes in a 375° preheated oven.
Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cake mix, sour cream and eggs in large bowl until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan; mix and pour batter into pan.
Mix blackberries, water and sugar in bowl; pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and 3 cups milk.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: coconut chews
directions: Cook butter, sugar, dates and egg for 11 minutes over direct heat.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and walnuts.
Drop from spoon into coconut and roll into balls.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Stir in crumbs, onions, parsley, garlic, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Mix into ground turkey.
Broil until cooked through.

title: mustard grilled boneless chicken breasts
directions: Paint chicken breasts on both sides with mustard.
Sprinkle lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce over and allow to marinate at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes.
Preheat broiler or outdoor grill.
Grill chicken for 3 to 4 minutes each side or until just tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve hot.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix vegetables, seasoning packet, water and margarine in a bowl; add crumbs; stir until water is absorbed.
Mix gravy, chicken, vegetables and thyme in a 2-quart casserole.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add oil and milk; mix well.
Roll to size you want.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice and add alternately with dry ingredients to egg/sugar mixture.
Mix until smooth; add vanilla and beat well.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: crock pot ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in Crock Pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half, spoon undiluted soup over top, seal edges.
Cover and cook on Low 8-10 hours or High 4 hours.
Stir well and serve.

title: aunt shirley's chocolate cake
directions: *1 square of chocolate is equal to 3 Tbsp. cocoa baking powder plus 1 Tbsp. shortening.

title: orange buttermilk molded salad
directions: Bring pineapple with syrup to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk; fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into 8 cup molds and chill 4 hours.

title: cheesy turnips and carrots
directions: In a saucepan, combine turnips, carrots, ginger, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover and cook over medium-high heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain and reserve liquid. Set vegetables aside.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350°.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: May also use veal, lamb or chicken.

title: broccoli and cauliflower medley
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Put in greased casserole (2-quart) and bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: jackstraw eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise; peel.
Slice 1/2-inch thick. Cut slice sin 1/2-inch strips.
Beat flour, water, egg, oil, sugar and salt.
Dip eggplant in batter.
Allow excess batter to drain off.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot fat (365°) for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: a b's chicken wings
directions: For 20 Wings:
Boil water in large pot.
Drop in wings and boil for 8 more minutes.
Mix hot sauce, margarine and mustard in bowl.
Microwave in short intervals and keep stirring.
Then add Good Seasons package.
Brush on wings and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Do not turn wings during cooking.

title: potato o'brien
directions: Place in a baking dish in order listed.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top of first 5 ingredients.
Drizzle margarine over top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order and put in greased pan (I use a bundt pan). Bake at 325 for 1 hour. Allow cake to remain in pan and cover with glaze.

title: molly's breakfast "egg thing"
directions: Alternate layers of bread, cheeses and olives in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour over layers. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple salsa
directions: Season sliced cucumbers with salt and fresh or dried dill weed.
Cover with sour cream and chill for 1 or 2 hours.

title: coal flowers
directions: Place a piece of coal in a deep glass dish.
Pour the liquid around the coal, but not on it.
Dot the coal with the red ink. Do not move the dish and coral-like crystals will soon appear and spread over the coal.
They will grow to a height of about 1/2-inch in a sponge-like appearance and will last for weeks.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and add, alternating with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and thoroughly cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, and cream.
Add chocolate, which has been melted, and vanilla.
Gradually fold in sifted flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Makes two 10-inch layers or three 8-inch layers.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Combine and bring to a boil spices, brown sugar, 1/3 cup water and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Pour over cooked sweet potato halves arranged in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is somewhat thickened.
Baste frequently while baking.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin together in large bowl. Combine rest of ingredients in a separate bowl, then add to pumpkin mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Place chicken in buttered baking dish. Mix sour cream and soup.
Add peas and carrots; mix.
If needed, add some broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
If using grated cheese, omit margarine and top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients, using just enough flour to be able to roll out and cut into fat cookies. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden.
Sprinkle with sugar on tops before baking (optional).

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Chill until set, 3 to 4 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: super seafood spread
directions: Place seafood of your choice in mixing bowl.
Break up finely with fork.
Add remaining ingredients except olives.
Mix well. Chill.
Garnish with olives and additional picante sauce if desired.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: dr. carter's chicken #2
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Place in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Spoon on preserves and dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: High Altitude:
Decrease baking powder to 1 1/2 teaspoons.

title: a. b. c. salad
directions: Put in a large pan. Chill until firm.

title: bean dip
directions: Fry hamburger; season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Mix in chili.
Spread cream cheese in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread seasoned meat over cheese.
Top with diced green onions, tomato and green pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sausage cake
directions: Combine sausage and sugars until well blended,
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together four, spices, and baking powder.
Stir baking soda into coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee alternately to meat mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour boiling water to cover over raisins and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well and pat dry with paper towel.
Fold raisins and walnuts into batter,
Turn into well greased and floured Bundt pan (9c size). Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done at 350.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out of pan.
To store wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: surprise cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add sweet milk and beat together.
Pour batter into a greased pan.
Pour juicy fruit over batter and bake slowly about 35 minutes.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Sauce onions.
Add 2 cans soup, milk, corn, cheese and shrimp. Simmer until cheese is melted and flavors are blended.
Good served with fresh spinach salad.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate bits, peanut butter and margarine together. Stir in Chex cereal and marshmallows.
Dump this into a grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake.

title: broccoli-cheese appetizers
directions: Grease a square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick, water and oregano until dough forms.
Turn onto floured surface.
Gently roll in flour to coat.
Knead 50 times.
Divide dough into halves. Roll each half into 9-inch squares.
Place one square into pan. Beat eggs slightly; reserve 1 tablespoon.
Mix rest of eggs, broccoli and 1 1/2 cups cheese thoroughly.
Spread over square in pan.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until soft over low heat.
Turn up heat and add the meat, stirring until it is well browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar, Karo and oleo to boil.
Add peanut butter; stir until creamy.
Remove
from fire.
Add corn flakes.
Drop from spoon onto cookie
sheet, or pour onto cookie sheet. Cool and break.
(No baking.)

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix together sugar, dates, peanut butter, walnuts and butter. Shape into logs and chill for 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and dressing mix.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Stir well until absorbed.
Cover several hours and stir well again.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Blend until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers in a large dish.
Pour 1/2 pudding over crackers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Layer crackers again and repeat.
Finish with crackers.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti and rinse.
In large container, toss with 1/2 Wish-Bone dressing.
Cook Skroodles; drain.
Rinse.
Add to spaghetti and Wish-Bone dressing.

title: buster boy freeze
directions: Crust: Crush cookies and mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine. Pat all but 3/4 cup in a 9 x 13 pan. Freeze 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (it helps if they are room temperature) in a bowl.
Roll them into little balls and bake on a cookie sheet or baking pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, mix potatoes and broth.
Heat to boiling; cover and turn heat to low and cook gently 2 to 3 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Mix cornstarch with a little of the milk, blending until smooth.
Combine with remaining milk and salt; stir into potato mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring until mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and add cheese, parsley and butter.
Add vegetables and meat.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; then mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over vegetables.
Serve.

title: boneless chunky chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
In a blender add stuffing, parsley and cheese until fine. Melt margarine; dip chicken, rolling in stuffing mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Voila!!

title: boston baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Add baking soda and bring to a boil. Cover and let stand 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa; fold in nuts and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool thoroughly before serving.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and add ground meat.
Cook until brown.
Mix other ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix pecans, melted margarine and flour together, well.
Spread in bottom of 9 X 13 baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Beat until smooth, powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 Tablespoons milk.
Spread over cooled crust.
Beat until smooth pudding and 3 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with cool whip. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: lima beans in carrot ring
directions: Cook limas according to directions and drain. Saute shallots in butter. Add yogurt and parsley. Stir to blend.
Add cooked limas. Spoon into center of carrot ring. Serve immediately. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican cream cake
directions: Dump all together and mix.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until bottoms turn light brown.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on Ritz crackers; garnish with lettuce and tomatoes or fill pocket bread.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 425° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 350°.
Cut 6 slices cheese into pieces.
In skillet, brown meat and pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves. Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour and cheese pieces.
Turn into prepared shell and bake 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining cheese slices.
Bake 3 minutes longer.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato soup
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon and set aside.
To drippings, add potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine flour with small amount of milk until dissolved. Add to potato mixture along with remaining milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Tips:
Bacon can be omitted.
Cook vegetables in water as directed.
Add 2 tablespoons butter when adding milk.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange it in single layers, skins down, in melted butter in a baking dish.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven, 425°, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour excess fat.
Combine canned milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion and mushrooms to chicken.
Pour milk mixture over chicken and add paprika.
Cover dish with foil.
Reduce temperature to 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: In blender container, place orange juice, strawberries and pineapple juice.
Cover and blend until frothy.
Stir in carbonated water; pour over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 5 (8 ounce) servings.

title: fruit salad mix
directions: Mix and sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese; mix well.
Add all ingredients together.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Cool for 4 hours or overnight.
Any flavor jello may be used.
Orange is the original flavor.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour; pat mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix well until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: carolina pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Add eggs and beat mixture well.
Add vinegar, vanilla and nuts, mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This pecan pie is lighter and not as sweet as most pecan pie recipes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm and crumble in yeast.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Place in a Sally Lunn ring mold or tubular pan (I use a Bundt pan).
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 16 large servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and black pepper; set aside.
Cook rotini and drain.
Add Swiss cheese while still hot, then add to Miracle Whip mixture and add vegetables. You may use any or all of the different vegetables.

title: white chili
directions: Combine chicken and broth in 6-quart pot.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and skim off fat.
Bone and cube chicken.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until tender. Add chopped chilies, cumin, Tabasco sauce, oregano and cinnamon. Do this in original pot.
Add broth (6 cups should be left) and soaked beans.
Cook until beans are done.
Add chicken cubes and season to taste.
Just before serving, add 1 cup of shredded cheese.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Stir shortening, just to soften.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion in baking dish.
Melt oil in pan; add flour; stir until smooth.
Gradually add broth, mayonnaise or sour cream, salt and a little pepper.
Stir until thick.
Pour over taters; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in large bowl.
Put garlic powder, onion powder, dill weed and dressing mix on crackers.
Warm up the oil and pour over crackers.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain well, then add sauce mixture, oregano, salt and pepper.
Let simmer 10 minutes. Cook the spaghetti and drain. Add to sauce mixture, then pour into a large, greased baking dish.
Top with cheeses and arrange pepperoni on top. Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles and cheeses are melted.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Remove seeds from grapes; cut each grape into quarters. Slice apples and banana into small wedges. Lightly mix fruit in bowl.
Add Miracle Whip, lemon juice and vinegar.
Lightly mix. Serves 4.

title: apple cream cake
directions: Sift together all the dry ingredients. Stir in the apple and 1/4 cup nuts.
Combine butter, milk and egg.
Stir into the flour mixture and blend only.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch round pan. Spread sour cream over top.
Combine sugars and spread over the sour cream. Sprinkle on remaining nuts. Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with butter or whipped cream.
It is also good cold.

title: cheesecake delight
directions: Tear cake into small hunks and put in 9 x 13 pan.
Whip Dream Whip according to package direction.
Cut cream cheese into small bits and add to Dream Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Pour over cake and stir gently until all the cake is covered.
Pour pie filling on top and smooth so it will look nice,
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mash together. Add a small amount of milk if needed.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until needed.
Drizzle melted oleo on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through.
Very good.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Add melted butter or margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts; mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
(May freeze.)

title: bee's gooseberry pie
directions: Wash some gooseberries and put some sugar on them.
Boil them on the stove.
Rol out a crust and put it in a pie plate.
Put the berries in the crust and fold over the ends.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 450° oven until done.
Serves 6 to 8.
Put some ice cream on top and you'll swallow your tongue, honey!

title: company casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in shortening.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce and green pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni according to package directions and combine macaroni and ground beef mixture in a baking dish.
Season to taste. Gently spoon cream of mushroom soup into mixture.
(Put cheese on top before you bake.)

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: dottie's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer.
For 1 chicken or 6 chops.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Tear chicken into pieces and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream with chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with chicken broth.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pinto beans over cornbread.
Layer lettuce, tomato, onions, pepper, pickles and bacon.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice until smooth.
Pour over salad.

title: no bake cocoa haystacks
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to full boil; remove from heat.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with Ginger Cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large bowl until well blended. Flour and grease 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 (10-inch) tube pan.
Remove when cooled.

title: johnny applesauce cake(century old recipe)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and blend well.
Add beaten eggs and applesauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: ritz cracker treats
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar and nuts.
Pile 1/2 teaspoon mix on a Ritz cracker.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: korean wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except wings, in a large, glass bowl. Add wings.
Marinate overnight.

title: speedy scalloped spinach
directions: If using
frozen
spinach,
cook as directed.
If using frozen or canned, be sure to drain well.
Blend soup, seasoned salt, onion
and	milk.
Combine	with spinach and blend well. Spoon into
buttered
casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double chocolate mint chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, 3/4 cup mint-chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In another bowl, combine melted chocolate, butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually blend in flour mixture. Stir in remaining 3/4 cup mint-chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then drain fat.
Add Veg-All tomatoes and sauce, okra and onions.
Cook on medium heat about 20 minutes. When done, add spaghetti noodles.
Then cook until noodles are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You may have to add a little water to make it more soupy.

title: fried rice - grandpa lim's recipe
directions: Saute onion and garlic in cooking oil until golden.
Add chicken and cooking wine.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables, m.s.g. and salt.
When vegetables are soft, add cooked rice in small amounts, mixing it through vegetables.
Add soy sauce and mix well.
When ingredients are thoroughly heated, add sesame oil and toss.
Ready to serve.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer nuts and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake batter until covered.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes and turn out on large platter or cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Press with a fork and crisscross.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, milk, cheese and rice and mix in broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll in small balls about the size of a walnut. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in 12 Pam-sprayed muffin pans. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, salt and spices; add pumpkin, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; lower heat to 350°.
Bake another 40 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in almonds, raisins and rind.
Turn into 2 well-greased 7 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Yield:
2 loaves.

title: apple torte
directions: Pat 1/2 of this mixture into a cake pan.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients of crust together on medium speed until crumbly.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cut bread in 1/2 slices; lay on the bottom of a pie pan (ovensafe).
Mix salt in eggs.
Pour eggs on top.
Put ham, grated cheese, bell pepper and onion on it.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Put 1/2 sliced cheese on top.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce and chopped vegetables.
Frost the top with mayonnaise and cover with cheese and bacon.
This will keep in icebox for 2 days.
I usually make just half the recipe.

title: easy cheesy fudge brownies
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Prepare filling.
Heat butter and chocolate in small saucepan until melted.
Cool.
Mix chocolate, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl on medium speed.
Beat in flour on low speed.
Spread half of dough in pan.
Spread with cream cheese filling.
Gently swirl through dough with spoon.

title: quiche
directions: Prepare 1 (9-inch) pie crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 pound cooked bacon or crumbled sausage in shell.
Grate Cheddar cheese over meat.
Mix eggs, salt and half and half.
Pour into shell over meat and cheese.
Sprinkle pepper on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: skillet corn
directions: Rinse beef if salty.
Lightly fry beef and onion in oleo until beef begins to curl.
Stir in flour; add corn.
Heat until hot. Add milk, cheese, green pepper and olives.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve on buttered toast.

title: peppermint chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix chocolate chips, margarine and cream in heavy saucepan. Place over very low heat and stir until chips and margarine are melted and mixture is smooth and thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat in powdered sugar until mixture is smooth again.
Stir in peppermint extract.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours until mixture is thick enough to shape or drop into small candy cups.
Divide mixture into 24 portions.
Drop with No. 70 small scoop or roll into small balls before placing in candy cups.
Makes about 24 bon bons.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions (do not brown).
Add hamburger to onions and drain when done.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Add tomato sauce.
(Rinse cans so there will be enough water in sauce.)
Cook about 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry salt pork and onions until lightly browned; add water, potatoes and pepper.
Boil 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Heat fresh clams and clam liquor to boiling; add with milk to soup mixture and again bring to a boil.
Pour chowder over plain or crumbled crackers in a serving bowl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: Cook the first 7 ingredients until thickened. Cool in the refrigerator.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: shipwrecked casserole
directions: Layer ingredients.
Bake at 350° until ground beef is done.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix all together and set.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar in a saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm and slowly blend in oil, celery seed and grated onion.
Keep in refrigerator and use as needed.
This is delicious on fresh leaf lettuce.

title: lemon bites
directions: Mix flour, butter, and powdered sugar and press into 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Beat the rest of the ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes more. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. When done, shred chicken. Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with sour cream. Stir in chicken and put in casserole dish.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg; beat well.
Add the other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
(They have a better flavor when baked no longer than the light brown stage.)

title: mexene style shrimp
directions: Melt butter and cook onions until tender; stir in shrimp and let brown.
Stir in Mexene seasoning, flour, salt and gradually add milk.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato catsup, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Let steam a few minutes.
Serve over boiled rice while hot.

title: mom's pumpkin pies
directions: Beat all together at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, 1/2 pound sugar, corn syrup, extract and food color. Beat on low speed until ingredients are just blended. Increase speed to high; beat until stiff peaks are formed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Beat time is 7 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Mix ingredients with water, making a stiff dough.
Roll dough thin and cut into pieces about 2 x 3 inches.
Drop dumplings into broth.
Cover and reduce heat to medium, cooking about 5 minutes.
Do not stir dumplings.

title: chicken in mushroom soup
directions: Cut up chicken and wash.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup all over chicken.
Mix soup and pour over.
Bake in a 400° oven until chicken is done.

title: tri-tip marinade
directions: To marinade, mix seasonings and liquids.
Pour over your tri-tip. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Grill tri-tip and use marinade as a basting sauce.

title: holiday pate
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and add chicken livers.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup broth, sherry, paprika, allspice, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add the bourbon.
Soften the gelatin in the remaining 3/4 cup broth and cook over boiling water until dissolved.
Place the chicken liver mixture in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir the gelatin and walnuts into the mixture. Turn into or 5 or 6 cup mold or into several small molds and chill until firm.
Can be frozen.

title: simmered sirloin with noodles
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, cook beef, onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter over medium heat for 5-7 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink. Add the consomme, Worcestershire sauce and basil; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 50-60 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: 1. Heat oil in skillet. Cook onion over moderate heat until soft. Add meat and brown it.
2. Add rest of ingredients and cover. Cook over low heat
45 minutes stirring occasionally.
3. Heat oven to 350°. Do not grease pan. Put small amount
of sauce in bottom of pan. Lay in half the lasagna noodles (uncooked). Spread 1/2 the bucket of cottage
cheese, 1/2 mozzarella cheese.
4. Pour on half of sauce. Repeat layers. Top with parmesan
cheese. Bake 35-40 minutes until bubbly. Let stand 10
minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients except preserves and pack in a mold.
Fill center with preserves and serve with crackers.

title: pickled cranberries
directions: Boil with lid for 5 minutes (not berries).
Add cranberries. Let come to boil.
Stir gently not to crush berries.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator until served.

title: lady finger candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip round balls into this with fork.
Let dry on foil.

title: hornets nest cake
directions: Cook pudding until done.
Empty cake mix contents into bowl. Pour cooked pudding into mix; stir thoroughly.
Pour this into a greased cake pan.
Sprinkle pecan chips and butterscotch chips evenly over top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix flour and cocoa.
Add eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, then melted butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until pie has begun to set.
Don't overcook.

title: creamy brussels sprouts and noodles
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions. Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain well; rinse with hot water.
Cook onions in 2 tablespoons of the butter in a large frying pan, until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Blend in garlic, paprika, salt, caraway seed, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Fold in noodles and sprouts.
Spread in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle casserole and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb over batter.
Sprinkle sugar over and pour cream over top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Mix all together and knead.
Makes 4 double pies.
Roll out and bake according to type of pie you are making.

title: oven baked spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour over spareribs and marinate overnight, turning several times. Line shallow pan with foil.

title: perfectly easy dinner rolls
directions: STEP ONE:
Combine water and yeast in large bowl.
Let the mixture stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop vegetables and cook with ground beef until crumbly and slightly
brown.
Add
other
ingredients
and
bake in a covered dish for 2 hours at 300°.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Whip egg whites until very stiff.
Fold into mixture of all ingredients; stir until well mixed.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze at least 6 hours.
Bake at 275° until light brown.
Slice real thin and put on greased cookie sheet.

title: good 'n easy roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Add soup on top of roast.
Do not add water.
Cover.
Cook on high for 5 hours or until roast is tender.
Remove roast, then soup, which is now great gravy.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil together and cool the water and tea bags.
Combine all ingredients and freeze in a large plastic container that mixture can be scooped from.
To serve, scoop frozen mixture into a glass and pour 7-Up, Sprite or sour mix over it.
It is delicious and serves a large crowd.

title: stephen's favorite cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat margarine and sugars in large bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and crisp rice cereal.

title: mrs. will johnson's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil until well blended. Keep warm while using.
(Roast your meat; use sauce as desired.)

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a 2-quart pan, mix sugar and cocoa together until blended. Add butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
(Do not stir while boiling.)
Turn heat off.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until peanut butter is melted, then stir in oats. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: caramel popcorn bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine popcorn, cereal, M&M's and pretzels. Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix very well.
Put batter into small bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's orange bread
directions: Cut orange in quarters; remove seeds and white core.
Grind or use blender.
(Add enough water to juice and pulp to make one cup.)
Combine with oleo and salt; bring to boil.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast.
Beat until well blended.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for about 10 minutes on a well floured board.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk. Knead again.
Place in well greased loaf pan.
Let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix well; put in covered bowl overnight.

title: blu cobbler with cookie dough topping
directions: Mix together blueberries, 5 tablespoons sugar, orange juice and cornstarch; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the butter, 1 cup sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by tablespoon over blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
The topping should be golden brown.

title: pudding fruit dessert
directions: Drain fruit in a bowl.
Set aside.
Stir together pudding mixes.
Pour in liquid slowly with pudding mixes.
Mix well. Microwave on High until it boils and looks clean, about 6 minutes. Stir 2 or 3 times while cooking.
Cool.
Add fruit.
Chill for awhile.
Then serve.

title: pecan delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and stick of butter until fluffy.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Divide dough into equal parts.
Place in muffin tins and form into shells.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Make sausage balls and fry them.
Cook onions and pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and paste.
Add seasonings. Slice zucchini (do not peel) in 1/2-inch slices.
Add uncooked noodles and sausage balls.
Cover and cook until zucchini and noodles are tender, 45 minutes.
Pour in a greased casserole dish and cover with strips of cheese.
Place in a 350° oven.
Remove when cheese is melted.

title: pork hash with tofu
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for tofu, and mix well.
Place in a large bowl and flatten mixture around bowl.
Cube the tofu in blocks and place in center of bowl.
Steam 45 minutes over boiling water.

title: onion bread
directions: Heat all ingredients except yeast and flour. When WARM take off
stove and stir in yeast. Knead in the flour and let raise like other bread. Make into loaves and let raise again. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven. Makes 4 average loaves.

title: potato custard
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm in middle.

title: blender salad dressing(dietetic)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 3 cups.
Exchanges: 1 tablespoon = 1 fat. Calories: 1 serving = 61.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating.
Add flour slowly.
Add flavoring last and 7-Up.
Cook in tube pan, greased and floured, at 320° until done, 1 1/2 hours or so.

title: fruit pizza(12 servings)
directions: Cook until thick; cool and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate pizza.

title: sugar cookies (soft)
directions: Mix butter, cream and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix in vinegar.
Add flour, one cup at a time. Mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers and green onions in a large bowl.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and thinly slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix and bring to boil:
sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and soup.
Slice onion, pepper and celery thinly.
Mix with cooked carrots.
Remove sauce from heat and pour over carrots.
May be served hot or cold.

title: meal in a casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish and arrange vegetables in order given. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix undiluted soup with the uncooked ground beef in a separate bowl.
Spread the meat mixture over the top of the vegetables in the casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
When half done, cover the casserole dish with foil.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seeds; toast Ramen noodles.

title: candied carrots
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cook corn according to package directions.
Transfer corn to a serving platter and brush margarine mixture over corn.

title: lorenz family barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chicken, in saucepan and bring to soft boil.
Dunk chicken and place on outdoor grill. Continue to dunk chicken every time you turn it (approximately every 10 minutes).
Grill over medium for about 1 hour.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Icing:
Combine sour cream, sugar and frozen coconut.
Mix and leave covered overnight in refrigerator.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low setting 4 to 6 hours.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Beat egg white stiff.
Beat in sifted sugar.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 300°.

title: antipasto dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Heat oil in saucepan over medium heat; add onion and garlic and cook 3 minutes or until tender. Add vinegar and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables; cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: steak subs
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook beef, green onions, garlic and oregano until beef is brown.
Stir often.
Add in gravy.
Heat through.
Line bottom half of rolls with lettuce.
Spoon about 1/4 cup mixture onto each roll.
Top with cheese and tomatoes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine Cool Whip, lemonade and condensed milk, blending well.
Pour the mixture into crust and chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine corn syrup and sugar.
Mix well.
Microwave on High
(100% power) until the mixture boils, about 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Stir in peanut butter; mix until smooth.
Add chips, stirring until melted.
Stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Immediately pour into a greased and foil-lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until mixture is firm.
Remove foil from pan and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: tuna-macaroni pie
directions: Cook the elbow macaroni in a large amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain the macaroni and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt the butter; stir in the all-purpose flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the chopped celery, chopped onion and shredded cheese; stir until the cheese is melted.
Combine the cheese sauce and the drained macaroni.
Break tuna into chunks. Combine macaroni-cheese mixture, tuna, soft bread crumbs and beaten eggs.
Turn mixture into a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle tomato slices with salt.
Arrange the tomato slices and American cheese triangles on top the macaroni mixture in baking dish.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes more or until the cheese triangles melt and the tomato slices are heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Add beaten eggs, butter and milk to dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Freeze.
To use, thaw and reheat at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Use heavy foil.
On a square of foil, place 1/2 potato.
Top with onion slices, salt, pepper and butter.
Top with other half of potato.
Wrap tightly with foil and place on coals.
Roast for 1/2 hour to 1 hour, turning often.
With oven mitt on, squeeze to check doneness.
I roast the potatoes first, then when I am ready to grill the meat, I move the potatoes to an area with no coals until the meat is done.

title: carole's chicken
directions: Set aside chicken breasts.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Place chicken in a deep dish or bowl and pour marinade over chicken.
Marinate chicken overnight or for several hours.
Grill chicken over hot fire for 3 minutes each side.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems and set aside.
In a skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until well browned; drain. Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from skillet.
In hot drippings over medium heat, cook mushroom stems until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove skillet from heat; stir in sausage, cheese and crumbs.
Preheat.

title: make-ahead breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in a medium skillet; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread bread crumbs in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandmother's brunswick stew
directions: Stew chicken.
Save broth.
In a large pan, put corn, butter, beans, V-8, chicken broth, chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook all day.
Serve with homemade bread.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk; stir until moistened.
Turn dough onto a floured surface; knead lightly 4 to 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch; cut with 2 3/4-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
One dozen.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, tossing gently to mix well.
Makes 4 cups.
Serve homemade salsa over fried eggs, cold meats, poultry, hamburgers or as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream the butter and add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add bananas to flour mixture. Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together and pour over the first 4 ingredients.
Best made night before!

title: eunice vaughn's cocoa fried pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over moderate heat until thick; cool.
Put on your favorite pie crust or roll out canned biscuits.
Fry until done.

title: kona banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Stir in bananas. Add flour and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: savory pork and vegetables
directions: Cut green beans into 2-inch pieces.
In skillet, cook chops in 1 tablespoon margarine for 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides.
Remove.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms with rosemary until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Add soup, water and green beans; heat to boiling. Return chops to skillet.
Cover; stirring occasionally, cook over low heat for 10 minutes, or until chops are no longer pink and green beans are tender.
Serve with hot cooked fettuccine. Serves 4

title: meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly; shape into balls.
Roll in flour and brown in small amount of oil in electric skillet.
Place meat balls in kettle and add one 46-ounce can tomato or V-8 juice.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Use sauce as gravy.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil until sugar dissolves.
Combine sauerkraut and chopped vegetables.

title: honey biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add milk gradually, blending until well combined.
Place dough onto floured surface and pat into a 1/2-inch thick rectangle.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cornbread mix and oil.
Stir in corn, garlic powder and cheese.
Mix well and pour into greased (Pam) 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lobster bluff
directions: Place fillets in a saucepan.
Cover with water; add the salt. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover again with cold water.
Add the vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Serve with melted butter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Hollow out bread.
Fill with dip and serve.

title: always ready bran muffins
directions: Put wheat bran in boiling water and let stand.
In a separate bowl, cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Add together all ingredients and mix well.
Store in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator at least 12 hours before use.
Keeps well for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
If it turns brown on top, just stir before use.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Mix chocolate and butter.
Gradually blend in milk.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, eggs, coconut and vanilla. Gradually beat in chocolate mixture and pour into pie shells. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 4 hours.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine and boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over slaw. Put into containers and freeze.
Thaw to serve.

title: apple crumble
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 ounce flour in mixing bowl. Squeeze lemon juice over apple slices.
Toss apples with sugar mixture.
Put
in
ovenproof
baking
dish.
Thoroughly
mix butter,
remaining
flour
and
cinnamon.
Add
lemon rind and remaining
1/2 cup of sugar.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake
in
oven
at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Combine and fold all ingredients together.
Spread into pan or Pyrex dish.
Chill thoroughly, cut into squares and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and spread in a 9 X 13 inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat hard until light.
Add mashed banana.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Stir into creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Add walnuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool on rack.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions and let cool.
Prepare pudding mixes according to package directions.
Crumble half of the cake in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Layer with pie filling, pudding mixture, half of the pineapple, half of the whipped topping and half of the pecans.
Repeat the layering.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Chill for 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: eight-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion, carrots, green pepper and peas in glass bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over layers, sealing to side of dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients;	pour
into greased tube pan and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: boston butt roast(in crock-pot)
directions: Put Boston butt roast in crock-pot.
Fill halfway with water. Add remaining ingredients, stir and cook on low for approximately 8 hours or until very tender.

title: chocolate zucchini bars
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Add zucchini.

title: club cracker squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with Club crackers.
Bring oleo, sugar, brown sugar and milk to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture over crackers in pan.
Put another layer of crackers over mixture. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Spread over cracker layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut in squares.

title: egg and sausage ball
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cool.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add seasonings and bread cubes.
Fold in sausage and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: special orange tea mix
directions: Use 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all items together, except grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake until melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Combine cheese, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Knead with hands until well blended.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Chill and serve.

title: cream icing
directions: Boil milk and flour until thick and cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add to boiled cooled mixture.

title: mother's potato rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Combine potatoes, potato water, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until butter is melted.
When this mixture is lukewarm, add yeast and eggs. Work in 4 cups flour, 1 cup at a time.
When well mixed, work in 3 1/2 cups more flour.
Use last 1/2 cup on board.
Knead dough until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl, cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down and shape into rolls or loaves.
Brush with melted butter. Cover with waxed paper and allow to rise until doubled in size. Bake in 425° oven until brown.

title: skillet barbecue pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil about 5 minutes on each side.
Pour off excess fat.
Sprinkle celery, brown sugar, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper over pork chops.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover; simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add to flour mixture and blend.
Add nuts. Bake in 4 small loaf pans, well greased, for 45 minutes at 325°. Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Great for freezing.
Makes 4 small loaves or two 9-inch square pans.

title: russian summit tea
directions: In a pitcher or large container, combine all of the ingredients.
Stir until well blended and sweeten to taste. Serves 12.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla.
Melt butter in milk.
Gradually pour in potato mixture, stirring.
Beat gently with rotary beater until well blended and smooth.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rice and sausage
directions: Cook sausage and drain fat.
Add onions, peppers and celery; cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in rice and water chestnuts; heat. Add water as needed.
Try turkey sausage rather than pork.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic or paper bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper and shake to mix.
Add the chicken and shake to coat lightly. Remove the chicken and reserve the excess seasoned flour.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium heat.
Add the chicken and brown on one side, about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Turn the chicken and brown well on the second side, about 5 minutes longer.
Transfer the chicken to a plate and set aside.

title: spaghetti mexicali
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Saute onion and green pepper. Add beef. Cook until just brown. Add all other ingredients. Blend well. Bake in covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in little hunks; boil for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender (not done).
In a bowl, take eggs and whip with fork until fluffy.
Dice 1 medium onion.
Add the chopped green chilies.
In a casserole dish, put Cheez Whiz on bottom and sides of dish.
Put layer of squash; pour some of the egg mixture (eggs, onion and green chilies) over the cheese and squash.
Repeat layers until all is used up.

title: fried chicken marinade
directions: Mix diced green pepper with diced onion and garlic powder into cooking wine.
Marinate chicken breast strips for 1 hour, roll in cornmeal and fry until done.

title: honey-lemon dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk the mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, honey and white pepper until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: swanson skinny mashed potatoes
directions: In saucepan, place potatoes and broth. Over high heat, heat to boil. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain, reserving broth. Mash potatoes
with 1 1/4 cups of broth and pepper. If needed, add additional broth until potatoes are desired consistency. Serves about 6.

title: crab cheese dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Stir in crab, green onions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Wrap beef and bacon around chicken in a roll.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and spices; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: old-time giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add oil, flour, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend well; let brown.
Add 2 cups chicken broth (add more broth if needed).
Add giblets and eggs; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Serve with dressing.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Put in 2 greased round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until set.
Top with icing.

title: golden gate chow mein
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Brown meat.
Stir in celery, onions, soy sauce, Accent and broth.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and reserved mushroom liquid. Gradually stir into meat mixture.
Add Chinese vegetables, mushrooms and brown gravy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.

title: green bean au gratin
directions: Make a white sauce with the first five ingredients.
When thick, add cheese and melt.
Stir in green beans and pour into buttered 1 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, almonds and paprika.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Put onion rings on top during last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add oil.
Beat well. Stir in other ingredients.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sandwich pinwheels
directions: Butter a 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and blend well. Mix in melted butter, chiles and cheeses.

title: oatmeal pie
